WEBVTT

00:13.750 --> 00:15.792
DANIEL:  I was driving
to work this morning
thinking I will be here,

00:15.792 --> 00:18.125
in two months,
it'll be 10 years.

00:18.125 --> 00:21.625
And you're like
my real family.
Isn't that tragic?

00:21.625 --> 00:23.041
(ALL LAUGH)

00:24.834 --> 00:26.458
I got a call from my mother
this morning who wished me
a happy birthday

00:26.458 --> 00:29.542
and hinted around the fact
that I wasn't making
enough money.

00:29.542 --> 00:32.750
If you can call, "Are you
still making the same salary,
honey?" a hint.

00:32.750 --> 00:34.208
(ALL LAUGH)

00:34.208 --> 00:36.417
And my ex-wife used to
say the same thing

00:36.417 --> 00:38.083
although she never used
the word "honey."

00:39.166 --> 00:42.000
So maybe in three years,
I can double my income?

00:42.000 --> 00:43.125
Good luck.

00:43.125 --> 00:44.250
Four years?
Maybe.

00:44.250 --> 00:45.333
Okay.

00:45.333 --> 00:47.333
So you're great people
to work with

00:47.333 --> 00:49.500
and this is
a great present.

00:49.500 --> 00:51.959
And I wish I could
squeeze all of you
into one pretty woman.

00:53.333 --> 00:54.917
And if you'd like to go
into my office, I'll try.

00:56.166 --> 00:57.333
Thanks a lot.

00:57.333 --> 00:58.792
(ALL APPLAUDING)

01:06.333 --> 01:07.875
I'll be home in an hour.
WOMAN:  Why?

01:07.875 --> 01:09.166
I'm taking Daniel
to get his new car.

01:09.166 --> 01:10.834
I'm starving.
All right.

01:10.834 --> 01:12.792
What'd he get?
BMW convertible.

01:12.792 --> 01:14.625
Oh, my God. Leather?

01:14.625 --> 01:16.166
Leather?
Oh, yeah.

01:16.166 --> 01:17.291
Yeah.
I want one.

01:17.291 --> 01:18.667
All right.
Kiss Alex for me.

01:18.667 --> 01:19.792
I want one.

01:19.792 --> 01:20.875
She says,
"Happy birthday."

01:20.875 --> 01:22.834
Hey, these are
really great.
Thanks a million.

01:22.834 --> 01:25.166
Just stuff I like.
DANIEL: It's great.

01:26.250 --> 01:27.875
Why do you drive this?

01:27.875 --> 01:29.125
What?
I'm curious.

01:29.125 --> 01:30.875
I see people driving
these things.

01:30.875 --> 01:33.375
What do you know
that I don't?
Or flood's coming?

01:33.375 --> 01:35.208
Hoover Dam broke?
What's going on?

01:35.208 --> 01:36.375
I like this car.

01:36.375 --> 01:38.667
It's not a car.
It's a battering ram.

01:38.667 --> 01:40.583
This is what
Patton drove.

01:40.583 --> 01:42.708
(IMITATING PATTON)
Hey, you, soldier,
follow us.

01:42.708 --> 01:45.542
Make fun, but
in an 8.5 earthquake,
you'll beg for a Jeep.

01:45.542 --> 01:47.792
In an 8.5 earthquake,
I'll beg for a coffin.

01:47.792 --> 01:48.792
(CHUCKLES)

01:49.959 --> 01:51.000
So what are you
doing tonight?

01:51.000 --> 01:52.667
I'm gonna take
a long drive.

01:52.667 --> 01:53.792
Alone?

01:53.792 --> 01:55.000
Unless somebody
comes with the car.

01:56.208 --> 01:57.834
You don't want to be alone
on your birthday.

01:57.834 --> 01:59.542
What better day to be alone?

01:59.542 --> 02:01.291
I don't have that hang-up
like other people do

02:01.291 --> 02:03.583
about your birthday
and parties.

02:03.583 --> 02:05.750
You are born alone,
you should celebrate it.

02:05.750 --> 02:08.667
Celebrate aloneness.
That's what birthdays are for.

02:09.333 --> 02:10.542
Yeah, I never thought
of it like that.

02:10.542 --> 02:12.166
It's a pitiful theory.

02:12.708 --> 02:13.875
CAR SALESMAN:
Yeah, sure.

02:13.875 --> 02:15.041
WOMAN ON PHONE:
Look, I've had
these cars before

02:15.041 --> 02:17.041
and I know there's
something wrong.
Mmm-hmm.

02:17.250 --> 02:18.875
The smell is making me sick.

02:19.291 --> 02:21.500
That's a normal smell,
Mrs. Bernstein.

02:21.500 --> 02:24.250
That's a protective coating,
it's not oil burning.

02:24.250 --> 02:25.583
I think it's oil.

02:25.583 --> 02:26.875
You look fantastic.
You lose weight?

02:26.875 --> 02:27.917
Did I what?

02:27.917 --> 02:29.583
No, I was talking
to someone else.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.750
Did any of the lights
come on the dash, dear?

02:31.750 --> 02:33.208
I don't think so.

02:33.208 --> 02:34.542
Well, that means you're okay.

02:34.542 --> 02:36.667
If there's any trouble,
they come on.

02:36.667 --> 02:38.750
Mrs. Bernstein,
we have a little
saying around here.

02:38.750 --> 02:42.583
"If you really smell something
and don't see lights,
try dry cleaning."

02:42.583 --> 02:44.041
Try what?

02:44.041 --> 02:45.500
She has no sense of humor.

02:45.875 --> 02:46.875
Dry cleaning?

02:46.875 --> 02:48.250
Yeah, uh,
tell you what.

02:48.250 --> 02:49.917
If it smells on Monday,
you bring it in.

02:49.917 --> 02:51.583
I'm very worried.
I'm sure it's nothing.

02:51.583 --> 02:52.959
Well, I'm sure
it's something.

02:52.959 --> 02:54.375
Okay.
I'm on my way in.

02:55.208 --> 02:56.750
Trouble with one
of the new cars?

02:56.750 --> 02:58.291
Oh, no.
She's a lunatic.

02:58.291 --> 03:00.083
Boy, you have lost
a lot of weight!

03:00.083 --> 03:01.750
How could I lose
a lot of weight?

03:01.750 --> 03:02.875
You saw me three days ago.

03:02.875 --> 03:04.708
You look different.
Why? What is it?

03:04.708 --> 03:06.000
I don't know.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.583
I just wrote you
a check for $39,000.

03:08.083 --> 03:09.959
Ah, that's it.
That's the look.

03:09.959 --> 03:11.291
39 grand lighter.

03:11.291 --> 03:12.792
Let's go get it, huh?

03:12.792 --> 03:14.250
Let's get her. Whoo!

03:16.792 --> 03:18.083
Hey, what do you
got in the box?

03:18.083 --> 03:19.792
It's my birthday.
They gave me a
compact disk player.

03:19.792 --> 03:21.083
Hey, happy birthday.

03:21.083 --> 03:22.458
You got a CD
player in the car.

03:22.458 --> 03:23.583
No, I don't.

03:23.583 --> 03:24.792
You paid for it.
No, I didn't.

03:24.792 --> 03:26.250
You said you wanted
the best radio.

03:26.250 --> 03:27.875
The best radio
comes with a CD.

03:27.875 --> 03:29.250
Don't worry.
You'll love it.

03:30.291 --> 03:31.583
There she is.

03:31.583 --> 03:32.959
Wow.
It's gorgeous!

03:33.542 --> 03:35.834
Look at it.
It looks huge!

03:35.834 --> 03:37.959
It's beautiful!
Beautiful.

03:37.959 --> 03:40.125
That's not it.
That's a 750.
That's it.

03:41.333 --> 03:42.417
What a cutie.

03:42.792 --> 03:44.959
Gee, try not to show
the 750 first.

03:44.959 --> 03:46.708
My car looks like a turd now.

03:46.708 --> 03:47.834
I'm gonna level
with you.

03:47.834 --> 03:49.208
If I had to choose between
this car and yours,

03:49.208 --> 03:50.792
I'd take yours every time.

03:51.333 --> 03:52.917
You're an idiot, Jim.

04:03.875 --> 04:05.291
("SOMETHING'S COMING" PLAYING)

04:12.500 --> 04:16.125
♪ Could be

04:16.125 --> 04:19.625
♪ Who knows

04:19.625 --> 04:21.708
♪ There's something due
any day

04:21.708 --> 04:23.834
(SINGING ALONG)
♪ I will know right away

04:23.834 --> 04:26.834
♪ Soon as it shows

04:27.625 --> 04:29.667
♪ It may come cannonballin'
down through the sky

04:29.667 --> 04:30.708
♪ Gleam in its eye

04:30.708 --> 04:34.667
♪ Bright as a rose...

04:34.667 --> 04:36.333
(HORN HONKS)
Whoo!

04:38.208 --> 04:40.500
♪ It's only just
out of reach

04:40.500 --> 04:42.208
♪ Down the block
on a beach

04:42.208 --> 04:45.834
♪ Under a tree

04:46.041 --> 04:47.708
♪ Zubba dee be de be

04:47.708 --> 04:51.041
♪ There's a miracle due
gonna come true, coming to me

04:51.041 --> 04:53.208
MAN:  Do we all
have to hear that?

04:54.708 --> 04:57.208
♪ With a click
with a shock

04:57.208 --> 04:59.667
♪ Ba na blim bla
door'll knock, boop!

04:59.667 --> 05:02.000
♪ Open the latch

05:02.000 --> 05:04.250
♪ Something's coming
don't know when

05:04.250 --> 05:06.083
♪ But it's soon
catch the moon

05:06.083 --> 05:09.083
♪ One-handed catch

05:09.083 --> 05:13.875
♪ Around the corner

05:13.875 --> 05:18.875
♪ Or whistling
down the river

05:18.875 --> 05:23.667
♪ Do do do la la la

05:23.667 --> 05:24.917
♪ Come to me

05:24.917 --> 05:26.417
(HORN BLARING)

05:26.417 --> 05:27.875
(SCREAMING)

07:51.875 --> 07:54.959
Good afternoon,
and welcome to
Judgment City.

07:54.959 --> 07:56.500
You've just had
quite a little journey,

07:56.500 --> 07:58.834
so for now, relax
and enjoy the ride.

07:59.417 --> 08:01.917
Considering the transformation
you've just been through,

08:01.917 --> 08:03.417
you really won't have
any choice.

08:03.917 --> 08:06.291
Now, if we've done our
work correctly,

08:06.291 --> 08:09.417
you should all be from
the western half of
the United States.

08:10.208 --> 08:12.208
Even though this
isn't the Earth,

08:12.208 --> 08:15.708
our surroundings
should seem pleasing
and very familiar to you.

08:16.250 --> 08:17.834
Exactly why you're here

08:17.834 --> 08:21.667
and what you'll be doing
will be explained later.

08:21.667 --> 08:23.583
No need to worry
about that now.

08:24.458 --> 08:27.417
Soon we will be
dropping you off
at your hotel.

08:27.417 --> 08:30.041
You will sleep the night
and tomorrow when you wake,

08:30.041 --> 08:32.417
you'll feel wonderful
and raring to go.

08:32.958 --> 08:36.207
You'll find many activities
for your enjoyment
here in Judgment City.

08:36.707 --> 08:37.750
For example,

08:37.750 --> 08:39.375
how many like
to play golf?

08:41.457 --> 08:43.457
You won't be able to get
your hands up just yet,

08:43.457 --> 08:47.083
but good, we have three
championship golf courses.

08:47.083 --> 08:49.250
So sit back
and have fun.

08:49.959 --> 08:52.333
You're all gonna be here
for the next five days

08:52.333 --> 08:54.083
and we want you to
enjoy yourselves.

09:03.625 --> 09:06.333
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is the Continental Hotel.

09:06.333 --> 09:09.291
Those staying here will be
escorted from the tram.

09:09.291 --> 09:12.500
The rest of us will
depart momentarily.
Thank you.

09:12.500 --> 09:13.500
Watch your step.

09:16.959 --> 09:20.917
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome.
My name is Stan.

09:20.917 --> 09:22.291
Because of what
you've just been through,

09:22.291 --> 09:25.250
you'll want to go
directly to your room
and go fast asleep.

09:25.250 --> 09:26.625
You're already checked in.

09:26.625 --> 09:28.959
You have nothing to
worry about tonight.

09:28.959 --> 09:31.417
Everything will be
explained to you
in the morning.

09:31.417 --> 09:32.708
Have a good rest.

09:32.708 --> 09:35.583
If you have any questions,
I'm here to help.

09:36.000 --> 09:37.083
Thank you.

09:41.333 --> 09:42.667
Excuse me, sir.

09:45.291 --> 09:47.834
Mr. Miller, this is your room.
Make yourself at home.

09:47.834 --> 09:49.125
I'll be right back.

09:49.667 --> 09:50.834
This way, please, sir.

10:12.208 --> 10:16.625
Sir. All the clothing
you'll need for the time
you're here is in this closet.

10:17.875 --> 10:20.542
We call these tupas.
They're like caftans.

10:20.542 --> 10:22.792
They're quite comfortable
and they fit everyone.

10:22.792 --> 10:25.500
Would you like to shower,
or are you too tired?

10:28.708 --> 10:29.708
You're too tired?

10:32.208 --> 10:34.208
I understand.
There are five channels

10:34.208 --> 10:36.083
of programming
on the television.

10:36.375 --> 10:38.875
Channel 3 will tell you
all about Judgment City.

10:38.875 --> 10:40.250
Have a wonderful
night's sleep,

10:40.250 --> 10:43.375
and if I can do
anything for you,
I'm at your service.

10:49.000 --> 10:52.542
I'd be very surprised if
you found anything in there,

10:52.542 --> 10:54.583
but I appreciate the attempt.

10:56.417 --> 10:57.375
Sleep well.

11:16.291 --> 11:17.291
(SNORING)

11:18.625 --> 11:20.083
Good morning,
Ellen.
Morning.

11:20.750 --> 11:22.417
Good morning,
Philip.
Morning.

11:22.417 --> 11:23.917
Glad you could
make it, Leonard.

11:26.291 --> 11:27.834
Good morning, Susan.

11:27.834 --> 11:29.208
Good morning,
Mr. Diamond.

11:39.083 --> 11:40.250
Who's prosecuting?

11:40.250 --> 11:41.250
Lena Foster.

11:43.792 --> 11:44.750
Hmm.

11:46.500 --> 11:47.542
Huh.

11:48.875 --> 11:51.125
She's going to have
a field day with this one.

11:51.125 --> 11:52.959
She lost
last Thursday.

11:52.959 --> 11:54.375
Really?

11:54.375 --> 11:55.750
There is a God.

11:56.458 --> 11:58.125
Okay, call him up, please.

11:59.834 --> 12:01.417
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

12:06.166 --> 12:07.208
Hmm.

12:07.208 --> 12:08.500
(RINGING CONTINUES)

12:17.917 --> 12:19.458
Hello?
Mr. Miller?

12:20.000 --> 12:21.125
Yes?

12:21.125 --> 12:22.792
Hold on for Bob
Diamond, please.

12:22.792 --> 12:23.959
Who?

12:25.041 --> 12:26.583
DIAMOND:  Daniel?
Yeah?

12:27.000 --> 12:29.917
Diamond here.
How are you, my friend?
Good sleep?

12:30.625 --> 12:32.333
Yes.
Amazing, isn't it?

12:33.041 --> 12:35.792
Listen, you're gonna get up,
get showered,

12:35.792 --> 12:37.542
you're gonna put on
some of those nice clothes,

12:37.542 --> 12:39.208
you're gonna take
a tram downtown

12:39.208 --> 12:41.166
and you're gonna come
see me this morning.

12:42.083 --> 12:43.667
Do you have any idea
what's going on?

12:44.542 --> 12:45.542
No.

12:46.792 --> 12:48.667
Well, in a nutshell,
you're here to
defend your life,

12:48.667 --> 12:50.000
and I'm going
to help you.

12:51.333 --> 12:52.500
Defend my life?

12:53.875 --> 12:56.333
In a few hours,
you're going to be smarter
than anyone you've ever met.

12:56.333 --> 12:57.500
Sound exciting?

12:58.333 --> 12:59.500
Yeah, I guess.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.041
It is, believe me.

13:01.041 --> 13:02.834
Say, did you
eat breakfast yet?

13:03.500 --> 13:04.667
No.

13:04.667 --> 13:06.166
I've got some
good news for you.

13:06.667 --> 13:10.542
It's not only the best
food you'll ever have,
but you can eat all you want.

13:11.166 --> 13:12.166
I can what?

13:13.208 --> 13:14.083
As long as you're here,
you can eat all you want.

13:14.083 --> 13:15.792
It won't affect you
physically

13:15.792 --> 13:17.208
and you won't gain weight.

13:18.041 --> 13:22.083
So pig out! Eat 30 hotcakes.
I'll see you at 11:00.

13:23.500 --> 13:24.708
I can eat
all I want?

13:24.708 --> 13:26.750
Eat everything. Take care.

13:27.583 --> 13:28.542
(DIAL TONE)

13:29.708 --> 13:30.708
Hello?

13:44.208 --> 13:45.542
WOMAN ON TV:
You never loved me.

13:45.542 --> 13:47.333
You never loved me
for a second.

13:47.333 --> 13:49.500
MAN:
I've loved you from
the day I met you.

13:49.708 --> 13:51.500
When was the first day
you meet me?

13:51.500 --> 13:52.500
Do you remember?

13:53.375 --> 13:54.667
Don't do this
to me, Karen.

13:55.458 --> 13:57.083
Of course,
I remember.

13:57.083 --> 13:58.625
WOMAN:  What's
my middle name?

13:58.625 --> 14:00.083
You never told me that.

14:00.583 --> 14:02.083
It's the first
thing I told you.

14:02.417 --> 14:03.708
In which life?

14:04.750 --> 14:06.083
In which life?

14:07.417 --> 14:08.917
(CHANGES CHANNEL)
(STUDIO AUDIENCE GROAN)

14:09.875 --> 14:12.750
That's it, Lenore.
You tried, you failed.

14:12.750 --> 14:14.792
The game's over for you.

14:14.792 --> 14:17.291
Stay here and someone
will come and get you.

14:17.291 --> 14:19.625
Stu, the decision is yours.

14:19.959 --> 14:22.959
Do you want to stop here,
or face your fear?

14:23.583 --> 14:25.041
I'll face the fear.

14:25.417 --> 14:26.959
He's facing his fear!

14:27.458 --> 14:28.875
He's facing his fear!

14:31.750 --> 14:34.125
ANNOUNCER:  You might just
get a hole in one.

14:34.542 --> 14:36.792
Say, want to eat a lot?

14:36.792 --> 14:41.083
Ted's House of
Buffet says you can have
everything you see, plus more.

14:41.083 --> 14:44.250
Our chefs will cook it,
but they won't look.

14:44.625 --> 14:46.166
Like to horseback ride?

14:46.166 --> 14:49.083
Judgment Stables,
open till sunset,
welcomes you.

14:49.625 --> 14:51.458
If your trial's through early,

14:51.458 --> 14:53.458
come take a 2-mile
ride with us.

14:54.333 --> 14:55.458
You'll have fun.

14:55.667 --> 14:57.417
(MUZAK PLAYING)

15:04.375 --> 15:05.417
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

15:12.166 --> 15:13.333
Good morning.

15:13.333 --> 15:14.333
Good morning.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.208
"Take the eggs,
I pray thee."

15:23.834 --> 15:25.667
So, what's
good here?

15:25.667 --> 15:27.375
Everything we have
is sensational.

15:28.125 --> 15:30.208
How's the cheese omelet?
Sensational.

15:30.208 --> 15:31.875
I'll take it and
some orange juice.

15:31.875 --> 15:33.291
I'll be right back.

15:38.667 --> 15:39.667
(BELL DINGS)

15:43.333 --> 15:44.333
Whoa!

15:46.333 --> 15:47.333
Wow!

15:47.834 --> 15:49.667
This wasn't made for
somebody else, was it?

15:49.667 --> 15:50.959
No, this was made
for you.

15:51.500 --> 15:52.542
That fast?

15:52.542 --> 15:54.834
Fast and delicious.
Eat all you want.

15:55.500 --> 15:56.500
Phew.

16:01.375 --> 16:02.917
Oh, my!

16:02.917 --> 16:04.000
Mmm!

16:04.208 --> 16:05.375
Mr. Miller?

16:05.375 --> 16:06.667
Mmm!

16:06.667 --> 16:08.667
Delicious.
That's nice.

16:08.667 --> 16:10.375
A red tram is
leaving right now

16:10.375 --> 16:12.708
that will get you
into town by 11:00.
Mmm-hmm.

16:12.708 --> 16:14.208
Just to make sure
you're on time,

16:14.208 --> 16:15.667
I think you should leave now.

16:16.417 --> 16:18.250
These are the best eggs
I've ever had ever.

16:18.250 --> 16:19.417
Of course.

16:22.875 --> 16:24.083
WOMAN OVER PA:
Ladies and gentlemen,

16:24.083 --> 16:26.875
welcome to the Inner City
Transport System.

16:26.875 --> 16:30.667
Please remain seated
until the your vehicle
comes to a full stop.

16:30.667 --> 16:32.458
Never exit the tram
while it's in motion

16:32.458 --> 16:33.875
because of
the electronic field

16:33.875 --> 16:35.750
that's setup around
the moving vehicle.

16:35.750 --> 16:37.875
It is very dangerous.
Thank you.

16:56.083 --> 16:59.500
Oh, so young!

16:59.500 --> 17:00.750
AIDS?

17:00.750 --> 17:03.333
Oh, no.
Car accident.

17:03.333 --> 17:04.959
Oh, my God!

17:04.959 --> 17:07.959
But you feel
okay now, don't you?

17:07.959 --> 17:09.250
Yes, I do.

17:09.250 --> 17:10.583
Oh, me, too.

17:11.791 --> 17:15.000
Isn't it amazing?
Is this what you
thought it would be?

17:15.000 --> 17:16.625
I
certainly didn't.

17:16.625 --> 17:18.250
I don't know what it is yet.
Do you?

17:18.959 --> 17:20.791
No, I guess I don't.

17:27.208 --> 17:29.792
You make me think
of my little poodle.

17:31.500 --> 17:33.166
Do you have a dog?

17:33.166 --> 17:34.959
I did have a dog, yeah.

17:34.959 --> 17:35.959
Oh.

17:36.500 --> 17:38.583
Well, I'll tell you
about my dog.

17:39.750 --> 17:41.458
I had a little--

17:41.792 --> 17:43.166
Have you got a while?

17:43.166 --> 17:44.250
Yeah, go ahead.

17:51.417 --> 17:53.166
They let us
on the train
in those days.

17:53.166 --> 17:55.417
We didn't have to put him
in the baggage car.

17:55.417 --> 17:57.834
And every time
the conductor was
coming around,

17:57.834 --> 17:59.083
he knew it.

17:59.083 --> 18:01.917
And he would crawl down
in the corner of the bag.

18:02.625 --> 18:04.000
Did you ever
have a dog?

18:04.000 --> 18:05.458
You asked me that twice.

18:05.792 --> 18:07.208
What did you say?
Yes.

18:07.208 --> 18:08.333
What did I say?

18:08.333 --> 18:09.834
You said
it's wonderful.

18:09.834 --> 18:11.333
Well, it is.

18:15.708 --> 18:18.333
Mr. Miller, welcome.
I'm Helen,

18:18.333 --> 18:20.083
one of Mr. Diamond's
assistants.
Oh, hi.

18:20.083 --> 18:21.667
Would you come
with me, please?
Sure.

18:22.417 --> 18:24.125
Bye-bye.
Bye-bye.

18:27.000 --> 18:28.208
Looks familiar,
doesn't it?

18:28.208 --> 18:29.375
I was just thinking that.

18:29.375 --> 18:30.875
Well, that's how
it was designed,

18:30.875 --> 18:33.834
so it can be as stress-free
for you folks as possible.

18:33.834 --> 18:36.375
By the way, if there's
anything we can do
to make it more like Earth,

18:36.375 --> 18:38.542
we have suggestion boxes
on almost every corner.

18:38.542 --> 18:39.834
We'd like to hear from you.

18:41.333 --> 18:43.458
You know, if you really
want to make this whole place
seem more like Earth,

18:43.458 --> 18:45.834
you should start building
some of those mini malls.

18:45.834 --> 18:47.333
You know, it's funny
you should say that.

18:47.333 --> 18:50.000
Six of them opened up
just outside of town.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.542
I hear they're lovely.

18:51.542 --> 18:53.083
Personally, I don't think
I would use them

18:53.083 --> 18:56.208
because I don't like yogurt
and I love doing my own nails.

18:57.041 --> 18:59.208
Mr. Diamond
will be with you
in just a moment.

18:59.208 --> 19:00.500
Thank you.

19:16.500 --> 19:17.500
Huh!

19:21.083 --> 19:23.041
Daniel,
Bob Diamond.

19:23.041 --> 19:24.375
Hi.
Come on in.

19:25.375 --> 19:26.333
(BOOKS THUD)

19:27.250 --> 19:28.458
How are you?

19:31.125 --> 19:32.625
Sit down,
my friend.

19:47.583 --> 19:49.083
What are you looking at?
What's wrong?

19:49.083 --> 19:51.208
You... You look good
in that tupa.

19:51.208 --> 19:52.792
Some people don't,
but you do.

19:52.792 --> 19:53.959
It's flattering to you.

19:53.959 --> 19:55.041
Thanks.

19:56.125 --> 19:58.583
So, is this what you
thought it would be?

19:59.166 --> 20:02.291
Thought  what
would be?
Where am I? Is this heaven?

20:02.291 --> 20:03.875
No, it isn't heaven.

20:03.875 --> 20:04.959
Is it hell?

20:04.959 --> 20:06.583
No, it isn't hell either.

20:06.583 --> 20:08.417
Actually, there is no hell.

20:08.417 --> 20:11.333
Although I hear
Los Angeles is getting
pretty close.

20:12.125 --> 20:14.000
(LAUGHS)

20:15.333 --> 20:16.500
Well, Daniel,

20:16.500 --> 20:17.959
let me tell you
what's going on.

20:19.125 --> 20:21.125
When you're born
into this universe,

20:21.125 --> 20:23.083
you're in it for a long,
long time.

20:23.750 --> 20:25.959
You have many
different lifetimes,

20:25.959 --> 20:27.500
and after
each lifetime,

20:27.500 --> 20:29.917
there's
an examining period,
which you're in now.

20:30.667 --> 20:35.667
You see, every second
of every lifetime
is always recorded,

20:35.667 --> 20:38.250
and as each one ends,
we sort of look at it--

20:38.583 --> 20:41.250
look at a few
of the days,
examine it.

20:41.792 --> 20:44.250
And then
if everybody agrees,
you move forward.

20:44.959 --> 20:46.291
What do you mean,
move forward?

20:46.291 --> 20:48.667
I mean move forward.
Continue onward.

20:48.667 --> 20:52.166
The point of this whole thing
is to keep getting smarter,

20:52.166 --> 20:53.542
to keep growing,

20:54.000 --> 20:56.208
to use as much of
your brain as possible.

20:56.208 --> 20:58.333
For example, I use
48% of my brain.

20:58.333 --> 20:59.875
Do you know
how much you use?

21:01.834 --> 21:03.000
47?

21:04.375 --> 21:05.375
3.

21:06.000 --> 21:07.000
I'm sorry?

21:07.208 --> 21:08.208
3.

21:08.708 --> 21:10.000
I use 3% of my brain?

21:10.208 --> 21:11.500
Yes. Don't worry
about it.

21:11.500 --> 21:14.000
Everybody on Earth
uses 3% of their brain.

21:14.708 --> 21:17.000
3 to 5%.
That's why they're there.

21:17.542 --> 21:19.500
Three? 3%? 3%?

21:20.083 --> 21:22.333
You mean nobody on Earth
uses more than that?

21:22.333 --> 21:24.500
When you use more than
5% of your brain,

21:24.500 --> 21:26.667
you don't want
to be on Earth,
believe me.

21:26.667 --> 21:28.834
Well, not that your take-out
places are lovely,

21:28.834 --> 21:32.041
but there are more
exciting destinations
for smarter people.

21:33.041 --> 21:34.875
Now, being from Earth
as you are

21:34.875 --> 21:37.708
and using as little of
your brain as you do,

21:38.333 --> 21:41.792
your life has pretty much
been devoted to dealing
with fear.

21:41.792 --> 21:42.875
It has?

21:43.166 --> 21:45.667
Well, everybody on
Earth deals with fear.

21:45.667 --> 21:47.208
That's what Little Brains do.

21:48.583 --> 21:50.041
What are "Little Brains"?

21:50.375 --> 21:52.834
That's what we call you folks
behind your back.

21:53.333 --> 21:54.875
(SNICKERING)

21:58.083 --> 21:59.250
Forgive me.

22:00.750 --> 22:02.166
Who are you?

22:02.166 --> 22:03.500
Well, I'm just like you.

22:04.208 --> 22:06.166
I was on Earth
a long time ago.

22:06.834 --> 22:10.500
But I advanced,
I moved forward.
I got over my fears.

22:10.500 --> 22:12.000
And I got smarter.

22:12.000 --> 22:13.792
Did you have friends
whose stomachs hurt?

22:13.792 --> 22:15.792
Every one of them.
It's fear.

22:15.792 --> 22:18.291
Fear is like
a giant fog.

22:18.291 --> 22:20.875
It sits on your brain
and blocks everything--

22:20.875 --> 22:24.750
real feelings,
true happiness,
real joy.

22:24.750 --> 22:26.750
They can't get
through that fog.

22:27.250 --> 22:28.917
But you lift it,

22:28.917 --> 22:32.250
and, buddy, you're in for
the ride of your life.

22:32.959 --> 22:34.917
God, my 3% is swimming.

22:39.542 --> 22:40.750
What are you reading?

22:40.750 --> 22:41.917
You wouldn't
understand this.

22:41.917 --> 22:43.625
Just numbers.

22:43.625 --> 22:45.583
You read numbers?
Yes, sir.

22:46.750 --> 22:49.291
So I'm on trial
for being afraid?

22:49.291 --> 22:51.500
First of all, I don't like
to call it a "trial."

22:51.500 --> 22:52.875
Second of all, yes.

22:54.625 --> 22:56.417
Well, what if I'm guilty,
what happens to me?

22:56.417 --> 22:58.458
Don't think
"innocent" or "guilty."

22:58.458 --> 23:01.708
Worse comes to worse,
you'll go back to Earth
and you'll try it again.

23:01.708 --> 23:04.250
Well, what do you do?
You just keep going back
until you get it right?

23:04.250 --> 23:05.959
Well, you don't
keep going back.

23:05.959 --> 23:07.792
Eventually, they'll
throw you away.

23:09.458 --> 23:11.250
Have I been to
Earth before?
Oh, yeah.

23:11.250 --> 23:13.458
How many times?
Approaching 20.

23:13.458 --> 23:15.000
Is that a lot?

23:15.000 --> 23:16.250
I was there six.

23:16.250 --> 23:17.458
Oh, my God!

23:17.458 --> 23:19.375
So I'm the dunce
of the universe.

23:19.375 --> 23:20.500
Don't be silly.

23:20.500 --> 23:22.792
We've had people
who've been there
100 times.

23:22.792 --> 23:24.333
I wouldn't
want to hang out
with any of them,

23:24.333 --> 23:25.792
but we've seen them.

23:26.458 --> 23:30.208
If you're defending me,
is there a prosecutor?

23:30.208 --> 23:32.500
Damn good one.
Lena Foster.

23:32.500 --> 23:34.792
We call her
"The Dragon Lady."

23:36.166 --> 23:38.333
That's our prosecutor?
Mmm-hmm.

23:38.333 --> 23:39.708
Who does she work for?

23:39.708 --> 23:41.166
The universe.

23:41.166 --> 23:44.166
You see, the Universe
is like a big machine,
and you and I are parts.

23:44.166 --> 23:46.542
Now they don't want
a part to get through
unless it's ready.

23:46.542 --> 23:47.875
A bad part
gets through

23:47.875 --> 23:50.125
and the whole
machine breaks down.

23:50.125 --> 23:51.959
So that's what
we're here for,

23:51.959 --> 23:53.208
to make sure
you're ready.

23:53.208 --> 23:55.166
So what do they want
to look at exactly?

23:55.542 --> 23:56.875
I can't tell you
that exactly.

23:56.875 --> 24:00.125
But I can tell you
it's nine days
from your life.

24:00.500 --> 24:02.166
Nine days?

24:02.166 --> 24:04.917
So my trial goes
on for nine days?

24:04.917 --> 24:07.208
No. All the trials
go on for four days.

24:07.208 --> 24:09.250
Over that time, we're
looking at nine days,

24:09.250 --> 24:11.000
or episodes
from your life.

24:11.000 --> 24:12.667
Which days? Tell me that.

24:12.667 --> 24:13.875
I'm not allowed.

24:13.875 --> 24:15.166
Is that a normal number?

24:15.166 --> 24:17.208
High? Low? Is that
a good number? Normal?

24:17.875 --> 24:20.083
You're very concerned
about normal, aren't you?

24:20.083 --> 24:21.583
Kind of cute.

24:21.583 --> 24:23.792
I'd prefer seven,
but nine's fine.

24:23.792 --> 24:25.250
Some people have 12.

24:25.250 --> 24:27.417
Say, you're hungry?
Starving.

24:27.417 --> 24:28.917
I had one bite,
then I got on the tram.

24:28.917 --> 24:32.208
Well, Mr. All-You-Can-Eat,
let's stuff. Come on.

24:36.083 --> 24:37.208
DANIEL: Mmm! Mm!

24:38.208 --> 24:40.834
We have about
400,000 residents here.

24:40.834 --> 24:43.000
We service half
of the United States' dead.

24:43.000 --> 24:45.083
That's about
2,500 people a day.

24:45.083 --> 24:46.083
Good.

24:47.041 --> 24:49.000
Do children
come here?

24:49.000 --> 24:51.542
Children don't have
to defend themselves.

24:51.542 --> 24:54.708
When a child is taken,
they automatically
move forward.

24:54.708 --> 24:55.917
Isn't that nice?

24:55.917 --> 24:57.834
Mmm, what about
teenagers?

24:57.834 --> 24:59.625
Too much trouble.
They go elsewhere.

24:59.625 --> 25:02.333
We tried for a while,
but they damaged the tupas.

25:02.333 --> 25:04.083
Too rowdy.

25:04.083 --> 25:05.792
What about your chicken?
How do you like?

25:05.792 --> 25:07.250
Oh, delicious.
Yeah.

25:13.417 --> 25:14.917
Mmm.
What are you eating?

25:14.917 --> 25:17.291
Oh, you wouldn't
like this. (CHUCKLES)

25:17.291 --> 25:19.417
What is it?
What does it taste like?

25:20.500 --> 25:22.250
You're curious,
aren't you?

25:22.250 --> 25:23.875
Good! I like
that about you.

25:24.917 --> 25:26.458
You want to try?
Yeah.

25:26.458 --> 25:28.250
It looks so weird.

25:30.583 --> 25:31.625
(SPITS)

25:31.625 --> 25:32.708
(LAUGHS)

25:33.417 --> 25:34.583
Oh, my God.

25:34.583 --> 25:35.917
A little like
horse shit, huh?

25:35.917 --> 25:36.959
(GAGS)

25:37.750 --> 25:40.583
As you get smarter,
you manipulate your senses.

25:40.583 --> 25:42.917
This tastes much
different to me,
than it does to you.

25:42.917 --> 25:44.667
Ooh! (GAGS)

25:44.667 --> 25:46.458
This is what
smart people eat?

25:47.834 --> 25:49.291
So talk to me, Daniel.

25:49.291 --> 25:50.500
Tell me about your life.

25:51.083 --> 25:52.792
You feel you had
any problems?

25:53.708 --> 25:55.500
Well, sure I had
some problems.

25:55.500 --> 25:58.000
Everybody has
problems, don't they?

25:58.000 --> 26:00.667
Everybody on earth.
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

26:00.667 --> 26:02.583
Did you give
a lot to charity?

26:03.125 --> 26:04.792
What do you
mean a lot?

26:04.792 --> 26:07.000
A lot of money.
Did you donate things?

26:07.500 --> 26:09.125
This isn't
a good or bad thing.

26:09.125 --> 26:11.000
It's just merely
my curiosity.

26:12.083 --> 26:14.125
Well, I mean, I'm sure
I could have given more.

26:16.458 --> 26:18.458
I gave a lot to people
on the street,

26:18.458 --> 26:19.625
but you never
get a receipt.

26:22.667 --> 26:24.125
How much do
you have to give?

26:24.125 --> 26:25.500
What's the total?

26:25.500 --> 26:27.166
Don't worry about it.

26:27.166 --> 26:28.208
Relax!

26:29.667 --> 26:34.208
But there was one person
you were really cheap
with over and over again.

26:34.208 --> 26:36.166
I wish you'd been
more generous with him.

26:36.166 --> 26:37.166
Who?

26:37.750 --> 26:38.875
You.

26:38.875 --> 26:41.166
Well, I got to go.
I'm late.

26:41.166 --> 26:42.208
Where do you go now?

26:42.708 --> 26:44.417
You wouldn't understand.

26:44.417 --> 26:45.875
I don't mean
that as an insult.

26:45.875 --> 26:47.708
I mean it literally.

26:48.500 --> 26:50.834
Get out tonight.
Have some fun.

26:50.834 --> 26:52.667
Say, you know
what you might try?

26:53.000 --> 26:55.166
Get over the
past lives pavilion.

26:55.166 --> 26:56.291
What is that?

26:56.291 --> 26:58.875
It's where
you see the people
you've been before.

26:58.875 --> 27:00.458
What?
Yeah.

27:00.458 --> 27:02.375
You see yourself
in other lives?
Yeah.

27:02.375 --> 27:04.959
Most people love it.
But some
it makes nauseous.

27:04.959 --> 27:06.125
(LAUGHS)

27:06.125 --> 27:08.208
Don't worry about it.

27:08.208 --> 27:10.667
All right. Take care.

27:11.542 --> 27:12.708
Listen, you
like that chicken?

27:12.708 --> 27:13.875
You want to
take it with you?

27:13.875 --> 27:16.000
They love putting things
in bags around here.

27:16.000 --> 27:18.083
If you need to talk
to me at any time,

27:18.083 --> 27:19.250
just call me up.

27:19.250 --> 27:21.208
I never sleep.
Never?

27:23.458 --> 27:25.041
Well, I had
another question.
See ya'.

27:25.041 --> 27:26.667
Okay, I'll call you later.

27:38.750 --> 27:39.875
MAN:  Already checked in.

27:39.875 --> 27:42.458
You have nothing
to worry about tonight.

27:42.458 --> 27:43.625
(SCOFFS)

27:43.625 --> 27:45.625
Everything will be explained
to you in the morning.

27:45.625 --> 27:47.041
Have a good rest.

27:47.041 --> 27:49.708
If you have any questions,
I'm here to help.

27:49.708 --> 27:50.750
Thank you.

27:58.250 --> 27:59.875
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

28:21.083 --> 28:22.750
If I told you
how old this man was,

28:22.750 --> 28:24.250
you wouldn't believe me.

28:24.250 --> 28:26.166
Should I tell them?
Huh? Should I?

28:26.166 --> 28:28.125
We're talking light-years.

28:28.125 --> 28:29.625
Light-years.

28:29.625 --> 28:31.333
He looks good, though.

28:31.333 --> 28:33.458
No prostate,
but he looks fine.

28:33.458 --> 28:34.959
(MAN LAUGHS)

28:35.792 --> 28:37.834
Come on.
You're looking at me
like stunned sheep.

28:37.834 --> 28:39.166
Come on, folks.

28:39.166 --> 28:40.500
What is this, a white sale?

28:40.500 --> 28:41.500
Come on!

28:43.750 --> 28:45.959
Well, folks,
I'm going to
tell you a story.

28:45.959 --> 28:47.500
About a year ago,

28:47.500 --> 28:48.917
this little brain
comes in here.

28:48.917 --> 28:50.583
I'm talking, and
this is documented,

28:50.583 --> 28:53.000
half a percent of
his brain, at the most.

28:53.000 --> 28:54.291
He orders a piece of pie.

28:54.291 --> 28:55.667
He forgets what it is.

28:55.667 --> 28:57.291
(INAUDIBLE)

28:57.291 --> 28:58.959
Well, I know what it is.
I'm looking
and it's a piece of pie.

28:58.959 --> 29:00.792
I say, "What the
hell are you doing?"

29:00.792 --> 29:03.125
He says, "I'm waiting
to make a call."

29:03.125 --> 29:04.667
I say, "Does that
look like a phone?"

29:04.667 --> 29:06.291
He says, "It is a phone."

29:06.291 --> 29:07.500
(CHUCKLES)

29:07.500 --> 29:08.625
Well, the joke was on me.

29:08.625 --> 29:10.125
He picked up the pie,
called his mother.

29:11.333 --> 29:14.333
Folks, come on, please,
stay with me here.

29:14.333 --> 29:15.834
You're on trial,
not me, okay?

29:16.750 --> 29:18.000
Hi. What's your name?

29:18.000 --> 29:19.166
Arthur.

29:19.166 --> 29:21.166
Hi, Arthur,
and where were you from?

29:21.166 --> 29:22.333
Denver.

29:22.333 --> 29:24.041
Lovely city,
Denver, Arthur.

29:24.041 --> 29:25.667
Did you ski?
No.

29:25.667 --> 29:27.166
No.

29:28.166 --> 29:29.333
How'd you die?

29:29.333 --> 29:31.000
I was in a coma.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.542
I'm sorry.
How long were
you in the coma?

29:33.542 --> 29:35.208
I really don't know.

29:36.125 --> 29:37.291
Let's play a game, Art.

29:38.000 --> 29:39.500
Elvis. Living or dead?

29:39.500 --> 29:40.667
Living.

29:40.959 --> 29:42.667
Long coma, Art.

29:42.667 --> 29:44.375
Long coma.

29:44.375 --> 29:45.542
Have a nice day.

29:45.542 --> 29:47.333
Hi. How are you?
What's your name?

29:47.333 --> 29:48.708
Ernie.

29:48.708 --> 29:50.542
Hi, Ernie, you having a good
time here in judgment city?

29:50.834 --> 29:53.208
Oh, it's fun.
Food's good.

29:53.208 --> 29:54.834
Yeah, it is,
isn't it?

29:54.834 --> 29:56.417
Have you been on the stables?
A little exercise?

29:56.417 --> 29:57.917
You like to
horseback ride?

29:57.917 --> 29:59.750
Not very much.

29:59.750 --> 30:00.875
Good.

30:00.875 --> 30:02.542
There's a nice-looking
young man over there.

30:02.542 --> 30:04.000
Hi. How'd you die?

30:04.000 --> 30:05.834
On stage, like you.

30:06.417 --> 30:07.667
(ALL LAUGHING)

30:09.250 --> 30:11.875
Pretty funny. Maybe you
should come up here, huh?

30:11.875 --> 30:13.208
No, thank you.

30:13.208 --> 30:14.875
Of course, he doesn't
want to come up here.

30:14.875 --> 30:16.708
You know why? 'Cause
this is very hard work.

30:16.708 --> 30:19.959
But I love to do it,
and I love you little brains.

30:19.959 --> 30:23.125
As a matter of fact,
have you heard any
new little brain jokes lately?

30:23.125 --> 30:24.417
Hi.
Hi.

30:24.417 --> 30:25.708
I know you, right?

30:25.708 --> 30:27.500
I hope so.
Who are you?

30:27.500 --> 30:29.875
I'm Julia.
Hi. I'm Daniel.

30:29.875 --> 30:31.166
Hi.
You know me?

30:31.917 --> 30:33.417
Well, I thought I did.

30:33.417 --> 30:35.291
You weren't in the bus,
were you?

30:35.291 --> 30:37.083
What bus?
I hit a bus.

30:37.083 --> 30:38.417
Oh, no,
I don't think so.

30:38.417 --> 30:40.208
Oh, good. Sit down.

30:41.417 --> 30:42.542
I'm sorry, I just...

30:42.542 --> 30:44.875
