in the schoolyard,

44:16.708 --> 44:18.667
did you want to
hit that child back?

44:20.250 --> 44:23.417
Well, I wanted
to hit him back,
but I felt restraint.

44:23.417 --> 44:25.500
You felt restraint.
I see.

44:26.583 --> 44:28.417
And do you think
that restraint

44:28.417 --> 44:30.792
is the best
course of action
every single time

44:30.792 --> 44:32.250
in every case?

44:32.250 --> 44:33.417
No.

44:33.417 --> 44:36.750
Wouldn't this have
been a case to
not restrain yourself?

44:37.875 --> 44:39.834
I believe, if you'd have
stuck up for yourself,

44:39.834 --> 44:41.583
this event would
not have haunted you

44:41.583 --> 44:44.083
throughout your
entire lifetime.

44:44.083 --> 44:45.875
You never got this
out of your mind.

44:46.375 --> 44:48.250
You always
thought about it,
didn't you?

44:48.250 --> 44:49.583
Hold on a second!

44:49.583 --> 44:51.250
People think about
lots of things

44:51.250 --> 44:53.041
throughout their
entire lifetime.

44:53.750 --> 44:55.417
You're going to isolate
this one incident?

44:55.417 --> 44:57.583
Aren't we here to
isolate incidents?

44:57.583 --> 44:59.750
Or maybe I don't
understand the job.

45:00.625 --> 45:03.333
Your Honors,
to save valuable time,

45:03.333 --> 45:05.750
I submit 11-4-19
as shown,

45:05.750 --> 45:07.250
without further comment.

45:08.125 --> 45:09.583
JUDGE:
Mr. Diamond?

45:09.583 --> 45:10.959
I'm fully satisfied.

45:10.959 --> 45:12.500
I love watching this kid.

45:12.500 --> 45:15.333
Mr. Miller, is there anything
you would like to say?

45:16.458 --> 45:19.125
I feel very good
about the restraint idea.

45:19.959 --> 45:21.166
Thank you,
Mr. Miller.

45:22.250 --> 45:23.750
JUDGE:  Mr. Diamond,
you're up.

45:25.125 --> 45:27.667
Your Honors, while
we're still in childhood,

45:27.667 --> 45:28.959
I'd like to show something

45:28.959 --> 45:31.834
which I feel is
absolutely extraordinary.

45:31.834 --> 45:33.917
Could we go to
10-9-15, please?

45:35.917 --> 45:37.625
(BEEPING)

45:44.208 --> 45:46.625
I'm on probation for
stealing those books.

45:46.625 --> 45:48.625
Now they're gonna
think I stole this.

45:48.625 --> 45:50.166
I'm gonna be expelled.

45:50.166 --> 45:51.750
You won't
be expelled.

45:51.750 --> 45:53.875
Of course I will.
I'm already
on probation.

45:53.875 --> 45:55.500
I'm in big trouble.

45:56.041 --> 45:57.041
(SHUSHING)

45:58.834 --> 46:00.333
Good afternoon, class.

46:00.333 --> 46:03.834
ALL: Good afternoon,
Mr. Wadworth.

46:03.834 --> 46:06.834
Continue working
on the assignment
you started last Tuesday.

46:08.500 --> 46:09.834
Here, take these.

46:10.375 --> 46:11.542
Really?

46:11.542 --> 46:12.875
I'll say I lost mine.

46:12.875 --> 46:14.250
But you'll
get in trouble.

46:14.250 --> 46:15.542
Just do it.

46:18.667 --> 46:20.708
Daniel, where
are your supplies?

46:20.708 --> 46:22.208
I left them at home.

46:22.208 --> 46:23.333
You left them?

46:23.333 --> 46:24.667
I lost them.

46:24.667 --> 46:27.041
What did you do?
Lose them or leave them?

46:27.041 --> 46:30.083
Well, both,
I left them
and I lost them.

46:30.083 --> 46:31.708
Where are your
supplies, Daniel?

46:31.708 --> 46:34.625
What's going on?
Do you know how
much these things cost?

46:34.625 --> 46:37.291
Class, tell Daniel
how much the paints cost.

46:37.291 --> 46:39.000
ALL: $10.

46:39.000 --> 46:40.417
And the brushes?

46:40.417 --> 46:42.208
ALL: $3.

46:42.208 --> 46:43.542
What's the total?

46:43.542 --> 46:45.708
ALL: $13.

46:46.542 --> 46:49.083
If you don't have
any paint, you can't
be an artist, Daniel.

46:49.083 --> 46:51.542
If just like you can't
be a swimmer unless
you get into the water.

46:51.542 --> 46:53.417
You've got to have paint,
you understand that?

46:53.417 --> 46:55.542
Yeah.
This is careless behavior.

46:55.542 --> 46:58.041
I'll have to
call your father
after school today.

46:58.875 --> 47:01.041
We're gonna have
to figure out a way
for you to pay for this.

47:02.208 --> 47:03.250
Yeah.

47:05.166 --> 47:06.375
(BEEPS)

47:10.583 --> 47:13.208
You got in quite
a bit of trouble for that,
didn't you, Dan?

47:13.208 --> 47:14.417
Yes.

47:14.417 --> 47:16.834
But you felt your friend
would have been
punished worse.

47:16.834 --> 47:18.041
Yes.

47:18.458 --> 47:19.792
Your Honors,
at 10 years old,

47:19.792 --> 47:23.208
he showed the
kind of courage that
most adults never find.

47:25.041 --> 47:27.250
I let the life
stand for itself here.

47:28.625 --> 47:32.250
Could we go to 10-9-15?
It's the evening
of that same day.

47:32.750 --> 47:33.750
Thanks.

47:35.917 --> 47:37.250
(BEEPING)

47:38.583 --> 47:40.458
How are you
gonna get the money
to pay for this?

47:40.458 --> 47:41.583
I don't know.

47:41.583 --> 47:44.375
I'm very, very
disappointed in you.

47:44.750 --> 47:45.917
I'm sorry.

47:45.917 --> 47:48.417
Now, we're gonna have
to punish you severely.

47:48.417 --> 47:49.583
You don't have
to punish me.

47:49.583 --> 47:50.917
Yes, we do.

47:50.917 --> 47:53.625
First of all,
no television
for a month!

47:53.625 --> 47:54.917
I didn't do it!

47:54.917 --> 47:55.917
Steve did it!

47:55.917 --> 47:57.083
It was Steve's fault.

47:57.083 --> 47:58.959
What are you
saying to me?

47:58.959 --> 48:00.333
Steve lost the paints.

48:00.333 --> 48:03.000
He probably stole them,
just like he stole the books.

48:03.000 --> 48:04.834
I didn't do it.
You've gotta believe me.

48:05.125 --> 48:06.291
Steve.

48:06.291 --> 48:07.333
Yeah.

48:07.333 --> 48:08.959
Hey, punish him.

48:08.959 --> 48:10.000
(BEEPS)

48:14.166 --> 48:16.458
What happened to
your friend Steve?

48:16.458 --> 48:18.291
Do you remember,
Mr. Miller?

48:18.708 --> 48:19.875
What do you mean?

48:19.875 --> 48:21.959
He was expelled from
school two days later.

48:21.959 --> 48:23.708
Isn't that what
happened to him?

48:23.708 --> 48:25.792
I thought he
left on his own.

48:25.792 --> 48:26.959
What's the point, please?

48:26.959 --> 48:28.500
I'm looking at the results

48:28.500 --> 48:30.792
of what you call
a courageous action.

48:31.375 --> 48:34.417
Mr. Miller might
have acted bravely
in the classroom,

48:34.417 --> 48:38.458
but we just watched him
crumble a few hours later,
and why?

48:38.458 --> 48:40.542
At the threat of
no television?

48:40.542 --> 48:42.708
I was 10-years-old.

48:42.708 --> 48:45.166
Television is everything
to a 10-year-old.

48:45.875 --> 48:47.000
It's like heroin.

48:47.000 --> 48:48.667
You can't just
pull it away.

48:49.083 --> 48:50.667
And I never wanted
to watch television.

48:50.667 --> 48:53.125
My parents made me
'cause they could go out.

48:53.125 --> 48:55.166
And I got hooked.

48:55.166 --> 48:57.375
You Honors,
Miss Foster and I
have had this argument

48:57.375 --> 48:58.875
for a long time.

48:59.333 --> 49:02.166
I think the act itself
is what's important.

49:02.166 --> 49:03.625
But she wants to
keep enlarging it

49:03.625 --> 49:05.834
until everything
loses its meaning.

49:06.375 --> 49:08.792
If I fixed a flat
tire on your car,

49:08.792 --> 49:11.166
and two years later
I lose your garden hose,

49:11.166 --> 49:13.375
according to you
I'm not going to get
any credit for the flat.

49:13.375 --> 49:15.458
I'm just the dumb
guy who lost the hose.

49:16.542 --> 49:18.125
And let me suggest this...

49:19.000 --> 49:20.417
Did we ever think

49:20.417 --> 49:23.250
that this young boy had
a bond with his father?

49:24.000 --> 49:26.250
I don't think
it had anything to
do with the friend.

49:26.250 --> 49:29.542
I just think Daniel
couldn't lie to his dad.

49:29.542 --> 49:30.583
That's all.

49:31.542 --> 49:32.959
You're nodding,
Mr. Miller.

49:32.959 --> 49:35.375
Does that mean you
agree with Mr. Diamond?

49:35.375 --> 49:36.708
Oh, yes.

49:36.708 --> 49:38.667
I had a bond
with my father.

49:38.667 --> 49:41.417
I pretty much
never lied to him.

49:41.417 --> 49:43.417
You never lied
to your father?

49:43.417 --> 49:46.542
Would you like me
to show you at least
500 examples?

49:47.750 --> 49:50.250
I said "pretty much"
never lied.

49:50.250 --> 49:52.250
I didn't say
I never ever lied.

49:52.250 --> 49:53.875
You have to lie sometimes...

49:54.708 --> 49:56.375
In an emergency.

49:57.208 --> 50:01.041
But it doesn't mean that
the bond is affected.

50:01.041 --> 50:03.208
If you've got the bond,
the bond's always there.

50:03.208 --> 50:04.458
And if you have
to lie occasionally,

50:04.458 --> 50:05.917
you not gonna interfere
with the bond.

50:06.583 --> 50:07.708
You know...

50:08.458 --> 50:10.542
The bond can wait
for a little lie.

50:10.542 --> 50:13.041
And in the end
it's there for you.

50:17.125 --> 50:19.834
You know, sometimes
in the middle of a lie,

50:19.834 --> 50:22.583
I found that the bond
would kick in,

50:23.208 --> 50:25.792
maybe squeeze
a little truth out.

50:25.792 --> 50:26.875
Psst.

50:27.458 --> 50:28.458
Wrap it up.

50:29.458 --> 50:30.792
I'm through.

50:32.083 --> 50:34.500
Very good day.
I'm very pleased.

50:34.500 --> 50:36.583
She's tough,
isn't she?

50:36.583 --> 50:38.250
If I told you
how tough,
my friend

50:38.250 --> 50:40.291
you wouldn't sleep,
believe me.

50:41.208 --> 50:43.792
Well, I'm off.
Call me if you need me.

50:44.458 --> 50:45.959
What are you doing
this evening?

50:45.959 --> 50:48.542
Going out with
that gal?
I can't. She's busy.

50:48.542 --> 50:50.333
Busy? Hah!

50:50.333 --> 50:51.917
Well,
I'll be damned.

51:20.000 --> 51:21.834
How are you?
All right.

51:26.625 --> 51:28.333
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

51:29.667 --> 51:30.959
Hi.

51:38.041 --> 51:39.417
How are you?
(SPEAKS JAPANESE)

51:39.417 --> 51:40.667
Thank you.

51:41.875 --> 51:43.500
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

51:44.041 --> 51:45.500
Uh, some sake.
Sake.

51:45.500 --> 51:47.166
One sake!

51:47.166 --> 51:48.834
ALL: (SHOUTING) Sake!

51:49.333 --> 51:50.792
How are you tonight?
Fine.

51:51.542 --> 51:52.708
Thank you.

51:53.708 --> 51:55.333
What's good here?
Everything we have.

51:55.333 --> 51:56.375
Everything.

51:57.041 --> 51:59.166
What's this?
Looks like a worm.

51:59.500 --> 52:00.834
That's our
resident food.

52:01.542 --> 52:02.500
What does it
taste like?

52:02.834 --> 52:03.834
You'll, uh, throw up.

52:03.834 --> 52:05.333
Okay. Let me
have the tuna.

52:05.333 --> 52:07.834
Tuna, sure.
Okay. Tuna!

52:07.834 --> 52:09.208
Very good tuna!

52:09.208 --> 52:11.333
Oh, very fast.
Very fast.

52:11.333 --> 52:12.708
So I've been told.

52:13.917 --> 52:15.375
Mmm. Delicious.

52:15.375 --> 52:16.750
Do you like it?
Very good.

52:16.750 --> 52:18.792
Thank you very much.
Very good.

52:18.792 --> 52:20.375
So how many days
are you looking at?

52:21.041 --> 52:22.125
Hmm?

52:22.125 --> 52:24.041
How many days
you looking at?

52:25.208 --> 52:26.583
Nine.
Nine?

52:26.583 --> 52:28.708
Mmm-hmm.
Nine days?

52:28.708 --> 52:31.041
Oh, my God.
Nine days!

52:31.375 --> 52:33.166
ALL: Nine days!

52:33.166 --> 52:34.542
(ALL SHOUTING)

52:35.375 --> 52:36.708
You better have
more sake.

52:37.708 --> 52:39.417
You got nine days?
Yeah.

52:39.417 --> 52:40.875
I got 15.

52:41.542 --> 52:43.375
My name's Frank.
Daniel.

52:45.333 --> 52:47.000
15 days?
Mmm-hmm.

52:47.000 --> 52:48.834
Is that a lot?
I don't know.

52:50.750 --> 52:52.583
How'd you die, Dan?
May I call you Dan?

52:52.583 --> 52:55.041
Yeah.
I got hit by a bus.
Ooh.

52:56.291 --> 52:57.583
What about yourself?

52:57.583 --> 52:58.917
Got shot
in the head.

52:59.333 --> 53:00.750
Really? Murder?

53:00.750 --> 53:02.375
No.
Hunting accident.

53:02.792 --> 53:04.959
Some putz with bad eyesight
thought I was an animal.

53:04.959 --> 53:06.250
(LAUGHING)

53:08.250 --> 53:10.417
How did you make
your living, Dan?
Advertising.

53:10.417 --> 53:11.792
What about yourself?

53:11.792 --> 53:14.417
I made money
in adult books.
Selling them?

53:15.083 --> 53:17.750
No, reading them.
Yes, of course,
selling them.

53:17.750 --> 53:19.250
(CHUCKLING)

53:21.417 --> 53:22.917
Were you from L.A.?

53:24.083 --> 53:25.959
You know those nightclubs
up by the airport?

53:25.959 --> 53:27.250
Those strip clubs?

53:28.792 --> 53:31.083
I coined the phrase
"all nude."

53:31.834 --> 53:34.333
What do you mean?
That was mine.

53:34.333 --> 53:36.458
I bought two of the clubs
that were going under.

53:36.458 --> 53:38.667
They were only using
the word "nude."

53:38.667 --> 53:41.291
I put up
"totally all nude."

53:42.000 --> 53:43.125
Mmm-hmm.

53:43.458 --> 53:44.792
Doubled business
in a month.

53:44.792 --> 53:46.208
I gotta take a piss.
You want to go?

53:46.208 --> 53:47.291
No.

53:48.166 --> 53:49.792
CHEFS: (SHOUTING)
Thank you very much!

53:51.708 --> 53:54.125
I'm not leaving.
I'm just going to
take a piss.

53:54.125 --> 53:55.667
CHEFS: (SHOUTING)
Take a piss!

54:12.959 --> 54:14.667
(PHONE RINGING)

54:19.417 --> 54:20.959
Hello?
MAN:  Mr. Miller?

54:20.959 --> 54:22.041
Yes?

54:22.041 --> 54:23.667
I have a message
for you, sir.

54:24.375 --> 54:25.667
You do?
Yes.

54:25.667 --> 54:26.708
Here it comes.

54:27.875 --> 54:29.667
JULIA:  Hi! Where are you?

54:31.041 --> 54:32.333
Okay.

54:32.667 --> 54:33.708
I'm going to sleep.

54:33.708 --> 54:35.625
Listen, tomorrow
when you're through,

54:36.333 --> 54:38.208
meet me by
the front entrance,
the main entrance.

54:38.208 --> 54:39.542
I'll be there.

54:39.959 --> 54:42.667
I miss you.
Isn't that funny?
(CHUCKLES)

54:43.375 --> 54:44.959
Good night.
(LINE CLICKS)

54:53.875 --> 54:55.250
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING ON TV)

54:55.250 --> 54:56.417
DIAMOND:  This is wild.

54:56.917 --> 54:58.375
Now, let me
get this straight.

54:58.375 --> 55:01.208
You actually had sex
with Benjamin Franklin?

55:01.708 --> 55:02.875
Twice.
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

55:05.083 --> 55:06.333
How was he?

55:06.750 --> 55:08.208
He was fat, Bob.

55:08.208 --> 55:10.000
AUDIENCE:  Ooh!

55:10.000 --> 55:11.583
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

55:12.917 --> 55:14.583
I couldn't believe it
when they told me.

55:14.583 --> 55:16.333
(CHUCKLES)
It's wonderful.

55:16.333 --> 55:18.000
I forgot all about it.

55:18.000 --> 55:20.250
He was willing to
sleep underwater.

55:20.250 --> 55:22.417
(LAUGHS)
Marvelous.

55:23.208 --> 55:25.417
Good morning.
Oh, good morning.

55:25.417 --> 55:27.750
Morning.
I'm Dick Stanley.

55:28.208 --> 55:30.417
I'm going to
defend you today.
You're what?

55:30.417 --> 55:32.375
I'm going to
defend you today.

55:32.375 --> 55:33.834
Now, Mr. Diamond
couldn't make it.

55:33.834 --> 55:35.166
I'm filling in
for him.

55:35.166 --> 55:36.208
He couldn't make it?
(CHUCKLES)

55:36.208 --> 55:37.708
Come on,
you're playing
with me.

55:37.708 --> 55:39.375
Mr. Diamond will be
back tomorrow.

55:39.375 --> 55:41.458
How can you defend me?
You don't know
anything about me.

55:41.750 --> 55:44.792
Mr. Miller I use
51% of my brain.

55:44.792 --> 55:46.250
I know everything
about you.

55:46.250 --> 55:48.250
51%? That's clocked?

55:48.750 --> 55:50.417
Clocked.
Impressive.

55:50.750 --> 55:53.208
Oh, I would lose.
I can't start
all over with you.

55:53.208 --> 55:54.625
(STUTTERS)
I have lots--

55:54.625 --> 55:57.083
No, I operate
a little differently
from Mr. Diamond,

55:57.083 --> 55:59.250
but without tooting
my own horn,

55:59.250 --> 56:01.041
I'm quite good at this.

56:01.041 --> 56:02.875
I'm familiar with
every day of your life

56:02.875 --> 56:04.583
and I want you
to have confidence.

56:04.583 --> 56:05.583
I'm going to lose.

56:07.208 --> 56:08.917
Good morning.
Good morning.

56:08.917 --> 56:10.041
JUDGE:  Good morning,
everybody.

56:10.458 --> 56:12.208
Thank you so much.

56:12.583 --> 56:13.792
That was so nice.

56:13.792 --> 56:15.125
Oh, it was nothing.

56:16.375 --> 56:17.417
JUDGE:  Good morning,
Mr. Miller.

56:17.417 --> 56:18.417
Good morning.

56:19.125 --> 56:21.333
Your Honor,
my defender is not here
this morning.

56:21.333 --> 56:23.000
And I feel that
under the circumstances,

56:23.000 --> 56:25.917
this puts me
at a disadvantage.

56:26.417 --> 56:28.667
It's quite common.
Mr. Stanley will do fine.

56:28.667 --> 56:29.750
Let's begin.

56:31.792 --> 56:33.625
(SIGHS)
Your Honors,

56:34.583 --> 56:36.959
today I would like to
begin with an episode

56:36.959 --> 56:38.959
in the 24th year
of life.

56:40.208 --> 56:42.291
Mr. Miller had been,
uh, out of school

56:42.291 --> 56:45.125
and working
for several years.

56:45.125 --> 56:49.750
And he had put aside $10,000
specifically to invest.

56:50.583 --> 56:52.125
Do you remember,
Mr. Miller?

56:52.834 --> 56:55.500
One of Mr. Miller's
good friends from school

56:55.500 --> 56:59.625
was the son of an executive
of the Casio corporation,

56:59.625 --> 57:01.542
which at that time
was a very small company

57:01.542 --> 57:03.333
and not doing
particularly well.

57:03.750 --> 57:06.792
Mr. Miller had a dinner
with his friend,
Your Honors

57:06.792 --> 57:09.333
at which he was
given information

57:10.208 --> 57:13.333
which comes along
maybe once every
five, six lifetimes.

57:14.417 --> 57:16.708
May we go to
24-2-16, please?

57:17.041 --> 57:18.708
(WHIRRING)

57:18.708 --> 57:20.333
(BEEPING)

57:21.250 --> 57:22.667
They're gearing up now.

57:22.667 --> 57:24.625
They should start production
in about three months.

57:25.041 --> 57:26.542
Buy as much stock
as you can.

57:26.542 --> 57:28.333
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

57:28.333 --> 57:31.667
Switzerland keeps
the time, Charles,

57:31.667 --> 57:32.708
not Japan.

57:32.708 --> 57:34.333
That's gonna change.
I don't think so.

57:34.333 --> 57:35.792
Wait, why can't Japan
keep the time?

57:35.792 --> 57:38.792
'Cause you need a society
that's into precision
to keep time.

57:39.500 --> 57:41.875
And with all due respect,
Japan makes a hell of a radio,

57:41.875 --> 57:43.834
but they don't know beans
about precision.

57:44.083 --> 57:46.708
Now, you come here,

57:46.708 --> 57:50.041
and you tell me
the Germans are going to
start making watches,

