you're at three.

57:59.417 --> 58:01.083
(CHUCKLES)
You watch.

58:01.083 --> 58:02.375
Remember who said it.

58:03.417 --> 58:04.542
(LAUGHING)

58:05.875 --> 58:07.500
(BEEP)
(WHIRRING)

58:08.875 --> 58:11.583
LENA:  Your Honors,
for the record,
the Casio corporation

58:11.583 --> 58:15.166
is one of the largest
manufacturers of timepieces
in the universe.

58:16.542 --> 58:17.750
I know
who they are.

58:18.875 --> 58:20.250
And for the record,
Your Honors,

58:20.250 --> 58:23.083
his original investment
of $10,000

58:23.083 --> 58:26.458
would be worth
37.2 million today.

58:26.875 --> 58:27.917
Wow!

58:29.583 --> 58:32.417
Mmm-hmm. I have nothing
further to say at this time.

58:33.291 --> 58:35.250
Mr. Stanley.
I'm fine.

58:36.208 --> 58:38.583
You're what?
He's not going to

58:39.792 --> 58:41.250
You're not gonna
say anything at all now?

58:41.625 --> 58:42.917
You speak.

58:42.917 --> 58:44.083
I'd like to hear
what you have to say.

58:44.417 --> 58:45.750
Jeez, you are good.

58:46.917 --> 58:50.250
Listen, (STUTTERS) I'm not
as smart as everyone here,

58:50.250 --> 58:53.125
but does this
make me defective

58:53.125 --> 58:55.417
because I didn't
make money on this?

58:55.417 --> 58:58.125
I can't believe that
the whole point
of the universe is...

58:58.125 --> 59:01.291
Is to make money.
(STUTTERS)
I just can't believe that.

59:01.291 --> 59:03.625
LENA:  This has nothing to do
with making money.

59:04.125 --> 59:06.500
We're looking at
a judgment you made.

59:06.500 --> 59:08.500
And nobody dragged you
from your home and said,

59:08.500 --> 59:10.542
"You have to
invest $10,000."

59:10.542 --> 59:11.959
You chose to do that.

59:11.959 --> 59:13.291
You sought
the investment.

59:13.291 --> 59:14.959
We're just looking
at that choice.

59:16.333 --> 59:17.959
What did you
finally invest in,
Mr. Miller?

59:17.959 --> 59:18.959
Do you remember?

59:21.041 --> 59:22.959
(SOFTLY) I think
it was cattle.

59:23.333 --> 59:24.750
Hmm?
(NORMAL) Cattle.

59:26.458 --> 59:27.667
What happened
to the cattle?

59:29.458 --> 59:30.792
I never got
a straight answer.

59:31.667 --> 59:33.500
All I know is,
their teeth fell out.

59:38.083 --> 59:39.166
I rest.

59:39.583 --> 59:40.959
Mr. Stanley,
you're up.

59:41.542 --> 59:43.125
No counter
at this time,
Your Honor.

59:43.500 --> 59:44.792
Wait a second.

59:45.458 --> 59:47.500
You're not going to
show something in my favor?

59:47.500 --> 59:48.917
Not at this juncture. No.

59:48.917 --> 59:50.542
I think we'd do better
to move on.

59:50.542 --> 59:52.875
(SCOFFS)
LENA:  Shall we move on,

59:52.875 --> 59:54.208
Sure, let's move on.

59:55.166 --> 59:58.166
Your Honors,
I would like to
go to 29-4-5.

59:58.834 --> 01:00:02.166
This is the evening
before Mr. Miller took
the job in advertising

01:00:02.166 --> 01:00:04.166
he was to hold
until his passing.

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:08.083
He asked his wife
to help him
by playing a little game.

01:00:08.083 --> 01:00:09.333
Do you remember,
Mr. Miller.

01:00:09.333 --> 01:00:11.041
You asked her
to act the boss

01:00:11.041 --> 01:00:12.500
so you could
sharpen your tools

01:00:12.500 --> 01:00:14.291
in order to get
what he wanted.

01:00:14.291 --> 01:00:15.333
(WHIRRING)

01:00:15.333 --> 01:00:16.667
(BEEPING)

01:00:18.083 --> 01:00:19.583
Do this for me.
It helps.

01:00:19.583 --> 01:00:21.667
Not now.
I'm eating.
Come on, do it!

01:00:22.458 --> 01:00:24.041
What do you
want me to do?
Be him.

01:00:25.041 --> 01:00:27.166
This is silly.
It's not silly.

01:00:27.166 --> 01:00:29.583
Offer me $55,000,
no more.

01:00:30.417 --> 01:00:31.500
How much
do you want?

01:00:31.500 --> 01:00:33.125
How much are you
offering me?

01:00:33.125 --> 01:00:34.750
$55,000.

01:00:34.750 --> 01:00:37.500
I can't work here
for a penny under 65.
I'm sorry.

01:00:37.500 --> 01:00:39.375
Well, I can't pay you 65.

01:00:39.375 --> 01:00:40.542
Then I can't work here.

01:00:41.417 --> 01:00:43.333
$58,000.
65.

01:00:43.583 --> 01:00:45.375
59.
65.

01:00:45.625 --> 01:00:48.208
60.
65.

01:00:48.542 --> 01:00:49.542
61.

01:00:49.792 --> 01:00:51.166
Let me make it plain.

01:00:51.166 --> 01:00:54.375
I cannot take the job
for under 65,

01:00:54.375 --> 01:00:55.708
under no conditions.

01:00:57.375 --> 01:00:58.792
Your Honors,
I would like to
go directly

01:00:58.792 --> 01:01:01.500
to the next afternoon
and show you
the real encounter.

01:01:03.667 --> 01:01:06.208
Daniel, I'm prepared
to offer $49,000.

01:01:06.208 --> 01:01:07.417
I'll take it.

01:01:09.750 --> 01:01:11.583
I'm going to get you
a parking place.
Okay.

01:01:16.041 --> 01:01:17.708
(BEEPS)
(WHIRRING)

01:01:24.667 --> 01:01:27.208
Why did you
cave in so fast?
I'm just curious.

01:01:28.417 --> 01:01:31.083
Why did you accept
so much less money
than you wanted?

01:01:31.083 --> 01:01:32.083
And do it so quickly.

01:01:32.542 --> 01:01:33.917
Here we go again
with money.

01:01:33.917 --> 01:01:36.083
Obviously, this is
all about money.

01:01:36.875 --> 01:01:39.834
Look, I'm guilty.
I didn't make enough money.
Okay?

01:01:39.834 --> 01:01:42.375
Call me a hippie.
Send me to hell.
I give up.

01:01:42.375 --> 01:01:44.583
You keep thinking
it's about money.

01:01:44.583 --> 01:01:45.875
But it's about fear.

01:01:47.625 --> 01:01:49.250
Why didn't you
stand up to your boss

01:01:49.250 --> 01:01:50.375
the way you did
to your wife?

01:01:50.375 --> 01:01:51.708
What happened
in your mind?

01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:53.458
Well, first of all,
it wasn't my wife.

01:01:53.959 --> 01:01:56.959
It was a man with a suit.
And the suit had a odor.

01:01:57.333 --> 01:01:59.583
And the odor
said $49,000.

01:01:59.959 --> 01:02:01.959
I like that very much.

01:02:03.542 --> 01:02:05.959
So your nostrils
told you you were
worth less?

01:02:05.959 --> 01:02:07.667
Is that what
you're saying?

01:02:07.667 --> 01:02:09.291
The process that
a person goes through

01:02:09.291 --> 01:02:12.417
when they're accepting
a salary is a complicated one.

01:02:12.417 --> 01:02:14.792
You don't know
all my reasons.

01:02:14.792 --> 01:02:16.417
Anyway, we lived fine
on that money.

01:02:16.417 --> 01:02:17.750
That money was fine.

01:02:17.750 --> 01:02:20.125
If you wanna make it
about money,
you may do so

01:02:20.125 --> 01:02:21.834
but we're looking
at fear.

01:02:21.834 --> 01:02:23.000
What was I afraid of?

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:24.083
You tell me.

01:02:24.083 --> 01:02:26.125
49 grand is
a lot of money!

01:02:29.417 --> 01:02:31.625
I have nothing more
to say at this time.

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:34.667
Mr. Stanley.
I'm fine.

01:02:35.583 --> 01:02:37.000
I can't believe it.

01:02:37.208 --> 01:02:39.166
And you didn't want to
toot your own horn.

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:41.333
Would you like
to show something,
Mr. Miller?

01:02:41.792 --> 01:02:43.708
I got a raise
six months later.

01:02:44.125 --> 01:02:45.708
Well, if you'd like
to show that,
let us know.

01:02:46.208 --> 01:02:47.375
Miss Foster?

01:02:47.667 --> 01:02:50.125
Oh, Your Honors,
at this time
I'd like to present

01:02:50.125 --> 01:02:52.375
a compilation of
general misjudgments,

01:02:52.375 --> 01:02:55.125
half of them fear-based,
half of them just stupid.

01:02:56.208 --> 01:02:58.917
I've assembled
164 misjudgments

01:02:58.917 --> 01:03:00.417
over a 12-year period.

01:03:00.417 --> 01:03:01.834
(SIGHS)
(WHIRRING)

01:03:02.917 --> 01:03:04.375
(BEEPING)

01:03:07.667 --> 01:03:09.166
Wait! Ooh! ooh!

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:11.333
(HORN HONKING)

01:03:11.333 --> 01:03:12.500
(SCREAMING)
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:03:12.917 --> 01:03:14.333
(HUMMING)

01:03:18.750 --> 01:03:20.041
(GARGLING)

01:03:21.750 --> 01:03:22.875
(EXHALES)

01:03:22.875 --> 01:03:24.208
Congratulations.
Thanks.

01:03:25.250 --> 01:03:27.041
(ENGINE REVVING)

01:03:28.208 --> 01:03:30.166
(BOTH LAUGHING)

01:03:48.291 --> 01:03:49.834
Whoa!

01:03:50.041 --> 01:03:52.083
(CRASHING)
(CHUCKLES)

01:03:52.083 --> 01:03:53.166
(CAT MEWS)

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.125
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:04:02.333 --> 01:04:03.750
Daniel! Hi!

01:04:04.542 --> 01:04:05.750
All right.

01:04:06.917 --> 01:04:09.708
Well, I can't tell you
how wonderful this is.
Oh.

01:04:09.708 --> 01:04:11.583
I'm looking forward
to tomorrow.

01:04:11.583 --> 01:04:13.250
Good night, Julia.
Good night.

01:04:13.583 --> 01:04:15.375
Hi. I missed you.
(CHUCKLES)

01:04:15.375 --> 01:04:17.083
Meet Sam.
Oh, hi.

01:04:17.083 --> 01:04:19.291
Hello, Daniel.
Julia has told me
a lot about you.

01:04:19.291 --> 01:04:21.417
Really? She doesn't know
that much about me.

01:04:21.959 --> 01:04:23.291
She could have
fooled me.

01:04:23.291 --> 01:04:25.291
Listen, I heard
you had Dick Stanley
in today.

01:04:25.291 --> 01:04:28.583
How did you know that?
Sam uses 54% of his brain.

01:04:30.083 --> 01:04:33.083
Dick Stanley's a good man.
Quiet, but excellent.

01:04:33.333 --> 01:04:34.417
Very quiet.

01:04:35.792 --> 01:04:37.875
Julia...
See you tomorrow.

01:04:38.083 --> 01:04:39.333
Yeah. Thank you.

01:04:41.625 --> 01:04:42.625
Bye-bye.

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:45.291
So we know
what we have to do.

01:04:45.291 --> 01:04:47.625
We have to go
to the past lives
pavilion.

01:04:47.625 --> 01:04:49.625
Everybody
talks about it.
I don't know.

01:04:49.625 --> 01:04:50.959
Don't you want to see
who you were?

01:04:50.959 --> 01:04:52.750
I heard some people
don't like it.
Oh, you'll love it.

01:04:52.750 --> 01:04:55.166
Plus, they have
the greatest hot dogs there.
What?

01:04:55.166 --> 01:04:57.083
Seriously,
the best hot dogs
in Judgment City

01:04:57.083 --> 01:04:58.583
are supposed
to be over by
the hall records.

01:04:58.583 --> 01:05:01.166
You really love
this eating thing,
don't you?

01:05:01.166 --> 01:05:02.500
To be able to eat
as much as you want

01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:05.291
and never gain an ounce
and feel great? Please.

01:05:15.625 --> 01:05:18.500
(GASPS)
Oh, wow!

01:05:18.500 --> 01:05:19.667
Look at this!

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:23.208
Oh, ho!

01:05:23.708 --> 01:05:25.667
(GASPS) Come on.
Let's get in line.

01:05:29.333 --> 01:05:31.291
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:35.708
This reminds me
of Disneyland.

01:05:36.333 --> 01:05:37.500
I hope we're tall enough.

01:05:37.500 --> 01:05:38.834
(LAUGHS)

01:05:39.250 --> 01:05:40.542
When you
were on earth,

01:05:40.542 --> 01:05:41.667
didn't you
ever feel like

01:05:41.667 --> 01:05:42.750
you might have been
other people?

01:05:42.750 --> 01:05:44.834
Did you ever see yourself
in another life?

01:05:44.834 --> 01:05:47.417
Never. You did?
(GASPS)

01:05:47.417 --> 01:05:48.792
I think I did.

01:05:48.792 --> 01:05:51.291
I think I might have
been a heavyset man
at one time.

01:05:51.291 --> 01:05:53.291
Really?
I doubt that.

01:05:54.041 --> 01:05:55.834
You never saw yourself
as anything?

01:05:55.834 --> 01:05:57.708
Well, one time in college
I got really stoned

01:05:57.708 --> 01:05:59.667
and I stared
into this mirror
for two hours

01:05:59.667 --> 01:06:02.166
until I finally saw someone
who looked Chinese.

01:06:02.708 --> 01:06:05.083
But I think it was
just me squinting.
(CHUCKLES)

01:06:05.875 --> 01:06:06.875
(CHUCKLES)

01:06:13.375 --> 01:06:15.875
WOMAN:  Please take the first
available booth on the left.

01:06:16.792 --> 01:06:19.375
The show will begin
in 3o seconds.

01:06:26.542 --> 01:06:28.208
(TRUMPET FANFARE)

01:06:32.708 --> 01:06:35.708
Welcome to
the past lives pavilion.

01:06:35.708 --> 01:06:37.083
WOMAN:  Oh, my God!

01:06:37.083 --> 01:06:40.375
In a moment you will be asked
to place your right hand

01:06:40.375 --> 01:06:42.375
on the plate next to you.

01:06:42.875 --> 01:06:46.625
An image of yourself
in a former life
will soon appear.

01:06:47.542 --> 01:06:49.041
When you have
seen enough,

01:06:49.041 --> 01:06:51.250
simply remove your hand
from the plate.

01:06:51.917 --> 01:06:54.959
Since we want to be fair
and accommodate everyone,

01:06:54.959 --> 01:06:58.083
you will be limited
to five past lives only.

01:06:59.125 --> 01:07:00.083
Thank you.

01:07:00.291 --> 01:07:01.458
(DINGS)

01:07:03.625 --> 01:07:06.208
Please place your hand
on the plate now.

01:07:11.208 --> 01:07:12.875
(HUMMING)

01:07:17.917 --> 01:07:19.291
What the hell is this?

01:07:19.917 --> 01:07:23.083
WOMAN:  Elizabeth!
Time for supper,
darling.

01:07:23.083 --> 01:07:24.917
Be there
in a moment,
Mumsy.

01:07:25.542 --> 01:07:27.291
What the hell
is going on here?

01:07:27.667 --> 01:07:28.959
(GROANING)

01:07:31.834 --> 01:07:33.250
(YELLING)

01:07:33.834 --> 01:07:35.458
(SCREAMING)

01:07:35.834 --> 01:07:37.291
(GROWLING)

01:07:38.625 --> 01:07:39.708
(SHOUTS)

01:07:39.708 --> 01:07:41.250
(LION GROWLS)

01:07:41.625 --> 01:07:42.834
(YELLING)

01:07:47.041 --> 01:07:48.125
(LION ROARS)

01:07:50.834 --> 01:07:52.542
Come on, men!
To the castle!

01:07:52.542 --> 01:07:54.917
Oh! (LAUGHING)

01:07:55.166 --> 01:07:56.917
(NEIGHING)

01:07:57.917 --> 01:07:59.417
It's incredible!

01:07:59.667 --> 01:08:00.917
Who are you?

01:08:00.917 --> 01:08:02.834
I'm Prince Valiant!

01:08:03.125 --> 01:08:04.625
Really?
Yeah.

01:08:05.667 --> 01:08:06.792
JULIA:  Who are you?

01:08:06.792 --> 01:08:07.792
Dinner.

01:08:16.291 --> 01:08:19.166
I was a prince,
I was a whaler,
I was a tailor.

01:08:19.417 --> 01:08:22.332
God! It was the most
incredible thing
I've ever seen.

01:08:22.332 --> 01:08:23.375
You were a native?

01:08:23.667 --> 01:08:25.542
Yeah, and a dressmaker,
that's all I saw.

01:08:25.542 --> 01:08:28.041
That's what, it's so weird,
you were a dressmaker,
I was a tailor.

01:08:28.041 --> 01:08:30.000
Isn't that interesting?
You want some?

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:31.125
No.

01:08:33.332 --> 01:08:35.457
You're gonna
eat the stick, too?

01:08:38.166 --> 01:08:40.000
I can't get you
out of my mind.

01:08:41.207 --> 01:08:42.834
Tell me about it.

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:46.542
You know, these screenings
are so tough, and yet,
when I see you,

01:08:46.542 --> 01:08:48.500
I instantly feel okay.

01:08:49.875 --> 01:08:51.707
That's great, right?

01:08:51.707 --> 01:08:53.542
I don't think it has
anything to do with me.

01:08:53.542 --> 01:08:54.707
That's what worries me.

01:08:54.707 --> 01:08:56.082
I think you're doing it.

01:08:56.082 --> 01:08:57.959
What? What am I doing?

01:08:57.959 --> 01:08:59.750
I'm not sure.

01:08:59.750 --> 01:09:02.834
But I always read that
you had to be okay
with yourself first,

01:09:02.834 --> 01:09:05.375
before you could be okay
with another person.

01:09:05.582 --> 01:09:07.417
And I feel
okay with you,

01:09:07.417 --> 01:09:09.375
but I don't know how okay
I was with myself,

01:09:09.375 --> 01:09:10.917
before I met you.

01:09:10.917 --> 01:09:13.417
So maybe you're
making me okay.

01:09:14.332 --> 01:09:15.917
You're not that okay.

01:09:16.917 --> 01:09:18.166
Okay.

01:09:24.417 --> 01:09:25.834
All right.
What's the score?

01:09:26.041 --> 01:09:28.041
(SIGHS) You're losing.

01:09:28.750 --> 01:09:29.875
No.
We're tied.

01:09:29.875 --> 01:09:32.082
Okay. Beauty.

01:09:32.417 --> 01:09:33.875
(EXHALES) Thank you.
(GRUNTS)

01:09:34.542 --> 01:09:36.417
You know what?
You never told me
how you died.

01:09:36.417 --> 01:09:37.959
How did you die?

01:09:39.207 --> 01:09:41.291
I don't want
to talk about it.

01:09:41.582 --> 01:09:42.750
Why?

01:09:44.125 --> 01:09:46.417
It's embarrassing.
Embarrassing?

01:09:46.417 --> 01:09:48.834
What could be embarrassing?
I was hit by a bus.

01:09:48.834 --> 01:09:49.917
(JULIA LAUGHS)

01:09:50.457 --> 01:09:51.959
I tripped.
No.

01:09:53.125 --> 01:09:55.291
Yes.
Seriously? You tripped?

01:09:55.291 --> 01:09:56.625
(CHUCKLES) Yes.
On what?

01:09:58.250 --> 01:10:00.667
We went to visit some friends
for the weekend.

01:10:00.667 --> 01:10:02.375
Everybody wanted
to go into town,

01:10:02.375 --> 01:10:04.750
but I wanted to stay
at the house and go swimming.

01:10:04.750 --> 01:10:06.208
So I went outside,

01:10:06.208 --> 01:10:07.417
tripped over
the chaise lounge,

01:10:07.417 --> 01:10:10.208
hit my head on the cement,
rolled into the pool.

01:10:10.792 --> 01:10:12.417
What did the East German
judge give you?

01:10:12.417 --> 01:10:13.625
(LAUGHS)

01:10:13.959 --> 01:10:15.542
So, seriously,
did you feel anything?

01:10:15.542 --> 01:10:17.792
Were you unconscious?
Were you scared?

01:10:18.375 --> 01:10:19.500
I was pissed.

01:10:19.959 --> 01:10:21.291
You died pissed.

01:10:21.291 --> 01:10:23.041
I'm still pissed.
I was a good swimmer.

01:10:23.041 --> 01:10:24.792
Well, swimming's only
part of the sport.

01:10:24.792 --> 01:10:26.291
You gotta negotiate
the patio furniture.

01:10:27.291 --> 01:10:30.542
You know, in the Olympics,
they're taking that
