There's too many people.

01:14:43.041 --> 01:14:46.000
I just looked.
There's too many people.
I can't go out there.

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:47.750
You've got to.
I can't go out there.

01:14:47.750 --> 01:14:49.083
Something has
happened to me.

01:14:49.083 --> 01:14:51.208
This is way,
way too many people.

01:14:51.208 --> 01:14:52.583
I'm having horrible
stage fright.

01:14:52.583 --> 01:14:53.875
I can't go out there.

01:14:53.875 --> 01:14:55.041
Hey, you got to
go out there.

01:14:55.041 --> 01:14:56.708
A lot of people
are counting on you.
Come on.

01:14:56.708 --> 01:14:58.333
I can't do it.
I'm gonna make
a fool of myself.

01:14:58.333 --> 01:14:59.417
No, you're not.

01:14:59.417 --> 01:15:01.375
I can't do it.
I can't do it.

01:15:01.375 --> 01:15:03.708
Yes, you can.
My heart is racing.

01:15:03.708 --> 01:15:05.959
I am having some sort
of an anxiety attack.

01:15:05.959 --> 01:15:07.208
Come on.
You know this stuff.

01:15:07.208 --> 01:15:08.417
You look great.
Let's go.

01:15:08.417 --> 01:15:09.583
Peter, I can't
think straight.

01:15:09.583 --> 01:15:12.125
Now listen to me,
that's too many people.

01:15:12.125 --> 01:15:13.250
I don't want
to go out there.

01:15:13.250 --> 01:15:14.708
You  have
to
cancel this.

01:15:14.959 --> 01:15:16.000
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:17.583
Let's go quickly,
you're on.

01:15:17.583 --> 01:15:19.250
Um, he's having
a little bit of trouble.

01:15:19.250 --> 01:15:20.959
Just give us
a second, all right?

01:15:20.959 --> 01:15:22.750
Let's go. You've got
a full house. It's packed.

01:15:22.750 --> 01:15:23.917
Let's go!

01:15:24.125 --> 01:15:26.500
Please don't make me
do this.

01:15:26.500 --> 01:15:27.959
You'll be fine.

01:15:27.959 --> 01:15:29.959
ANNOUNCER:  Good afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:15:29.959 --> 01:15:31.917
Would you please
welcome our speaker
for today?

01:15:31.917 --> 01:15:34.708
From Foote, Cone & Belding,
Mr. Daniel Miller.

01:15:34.708 --> 01:15:36.083
(APPLAUSE)

01:15:36.083 --> 01:15:37.875
I'll be right here
if you need me.

01:16:03.792 --> 01:16:06.458
Ladies and gentlemen,
may I have your
attention, please?

01:16:06.792 --> 01:16:10.000
Nothing serious, but we have
a gas leak under this room.

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:12.500
Ladies and gentlemen,
we'd like you all to file out,

01:16:12.500 --> 01:16:14.000
very orderly.

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:15.291
This is only
for precaution.

01:16:17.750 --> 01:16:19.500
(CROWD MURMURING)

01:16:27.583 --> 01:16:28.834
(BEEP)

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:31.333
Your Honors,

01:16:31.333 --> 01:16:33.375
I would have shown this day

01:16:33.375 --> 01:16:36.166
to illustrate just
how brave Mr. Miller is.

01:16:36.458 --> 01:16:40.125
With all the paying
and panic and confusion
going on in his mind,

01:16:40.125 --> 01:16:42.458
he still walked out
to that microphone.

01:16:42.458 --> 01:16:44.375
He never said anything!

01:16:44.375 --> 01:16:46.291
There was a gas leak!

01:16:46.291 --> 01:16:49.166
Yes, but he never went back
and accomplished it.

01:16:49.166 --> 01:16:52.834
He never got up in front
of a large group
of people again.

01:16:53.041 --> 01:16:54.708
Ha! Maybe he
didn't want to.

01:16:55.375 --> 01:16:57.208
Mr. Miller accepted
that speaking engagement

01:16:57.208 --> 01:16:59.041
with a great deal
of excitement.

01:16:59.041 --> 01:17:01.125
He wanted to be there.

01:17:01.708 --> 01:17:04.208
If he had accomplished
that moment,

01:17:04.208 --> 01:17:06.500
I believe that the rest
of his life would have gone

01:17:06.500 --> 01:17:08.875
in a much
better direction.
I'm positive of it.

01:17:09.458 --> 01:17:12.166
LAWYER:  You're positive of it?
This woman is wonderful!

01:17:12.166 --> 01:17:13.917
The rest of his life
would have gone

01:17:13.917 --> 01:17:15.667
in a much better
direction?

01:17:15.917 --> 01:17:17.375
Just incredible.

01:17:18.208 --> 01:17:19.417
(SIGHS)

01:17:19.417 --> 01:17:22.750
Your Honors, I'd like
to get off this scene

01:17:22.750 --> 01:17:25.667
and move on to something
that I think we'll have
a ball watching.

01:17:25.667 --> 01:17:28.417
This is damn
exciting stuff.

01:17:28.417 --> 01:17:31.250
Daniel, where did
this scene take place?

01:17:31.250 --> 01:17:33.333
I don't know what
you're going to show.

01:17:33.333 --> 01:17:36.834
Oh, I'm sorry.
We're going on 31-1-9.

01:17:36.834 --> 01:17:38.333
The snowmobile.

01:17:38.333 --> 01:17:39.792
Oh.

01:17:39.792 --> 01:17:41.208
Big bear.

01:17:41.208 --> 01:17:43.166
Big bear.

01:17:44.583 --> 01:17:46.583
Watch this, Your Honors.

01:17:46.583 --> 01:17:48.417
Just dynamite.

01:17:48.417 --> 01:17:49.875
(BEEPING)

01:17:50.208 --> 01:17:52.083
(HUMMING LOUDLY)

01:17:56.291 --> 01:18:00.291
♪ Where the buffalo roam

01:18:00.583 --> 01:18:02.458
(CHUCKLES)

01:18:03.417 --> 01:18:04.750
Oh...

01:18:05.125 --> 01:18:09.250
♪ And the skies
are all cloudy

01:18:09.250 --> 01:18:11.125
♪ All ♪

01:18:11.125 --> 01:18:13.208
Whoo! Oh, my God!

01:18:14.917 --> 01:18:16.542
Ahhh!

01:18:18.375 --> 01:18:19.708
Yeow!

01:18:19.708 --> 01:18:21.834
Oh!

01:18:21.834 --> 01:18:23.875
(GROANING)

01:18:26.250 --> 01:18:27.708
(SCREAMING)

01:18:32.708 --> 01:18:34.125
Ow!

01:18:34.125 --> 01:18:36.083
Oh! Oh!

01:18:37.291 --> 01:18:39.250
How far did you have
to go for help?

01:18:39.458 --> 01:18:41.166
About three miles.

01:18:41.166 --> 01:18:42.917
You broke that leg
in two places?

01:18:42.917 --> 01:18:44.333
DANIEL:  Yes, I did.

01:18:44.333 --> 01:18:45.458
I'm proud of you.

01:18:48.166 --> 01:18:50.291
(WOLF HOWLS)

01:18:51.333 --> 01:18:53.583
(WOLVES HOWLING)

01:18:54.250 --> 01:18:55.458
(BEEP)

01:18:56.417 --> 01:18:58.250
With no help,
by himself,

01:18:58.250 --> 01:19:01.125
with his badly broken leg,
as I've ever seen,

01:19:01.125 --> 01:19:04.208
this man crawled
three miles to get help.

01:19:04.208 --> 01:19:06.291
You can't be serious.
I'm sorry?

01:19:06.291 --> 01:19:09.917
What did we just watch?
That is self-preservation.

01:19:09.917 --> 01:19:11.375
He didn't risk
his life.

01:19:11.375 --> 01:19:13.000
He saved his life.

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:15.333
Oh, I see, you're not a hero
if you save your own life?

01:19:15.333 --> 01:19:18.708
A hero?
No, you're not. No.

01:19:18.708 --> 01:19:21.041
No one here
is accusing Mr. Miller

01:19:21.041 --> 01:19:23.166
of not having
a survival instinct.

01:19:23.166 --> 01:19:27.375
We're here to see
if he can overcome
fear, not pain.

01:19:27.375 --> 01:19:29.500
You don't see the fear
in this situation?

01:19:29.500 --> 01:19:30.750
What was he afraid of?

01:19:30.750 --> 01:19:32.834
Well, how about death,
for starters?

01:19:32.834 --> 01:19:34.542
I hope you realize,
Miss Foster,

01:19:34.542 --> 01:19:36.000
it would be very hard

01:19:36.000 --> 01:19:37.834
to be a brilliant
public speaker

01:19:37.834 --> 01:19:39.667
if you're lying dead
in the snow.

01:19:39.667 --> 01:19:41.667
Mr. Miller, for the record,

01:19:41.667 --> 01:19:44.166
you never rode
a snowmobile again,
did you?

01:19:44.166 --> 01:19:46.959
Wait a second.
Not because I was afraid,

01:19:46.959 --> 01:19:48.667
because I hated it!

01:19:49.500 --> 01:19:51.208
You have to
believe me on this.

01:19:51.208 --> 01:19:53.834
This has nothing to do
with fear. This is hate.

01:19:53.834 --> 01:19:56.667
This is a rotten contraption,
Your Honors.

01:19:56.667 --> 01:19:59.083
First of all, it heats up
like a toaster oven.

01:19:59.083 --> 01:20:00.750
I burned the hair
off my thigh

01:20:00.750 --> 01:20:02.583
from my knee
to my crotch.

01:20:02.583 --> 01:20:04.250
Singed it right off.

01:20:04.250 --> 01:20:07.041
Secondly, I don't know
if it was the leather-seat,

01:20:07.041 --> 01:20:08.542
or if it was lined with fur.

01:20:08.542 --> 01:20:12.458
But years of
rotting and drying out
and getting wet...

01:20:12.458 --> 01:20:14.667
Mine smelled like
an old sheepdog.

01:20:14.667 --> 01:20:17.750
Thirdly, it's very,
very noisy.

01:20:17.750 --> 01:20:19.250
They don't tell you
about that.

01:20:19.250 --> 01:20:21.417
You don't find out
until about the second hour,

01:20:21.417 --> 01:20:23.041
when you can't
hear anyone.

01:20:23.041 --> 01:20:24.542
You get off
and have a snack,

01:20:24.542 --> 01:20:26.875
and your friends
are in a silent movie.

01:20:27.375 --> 01:20:28.875
And fourth, uh...

01:20:29.750 --> 01:20:31.917
Pardon the expression,
but your balls vibrate

01:20:31.917 --> 01:20:34.208
for three weeks afterwards.

01:20:39.250 --> 01:20:41.125
I'm very proud
of you.

01:20:41.125 --> 01:20:44.083
Very, very good day.
Very emotional day.

01:20:45.125 --> 01:20:46.750
What are you
gonna do tonight?

01:20:46.750 --> 01:20:48.125
I'm gonna see
this woman.

01:20:48.125 --> 01:20:49.250
Julia?

01:20:49.250 --> 01:20:50.583
How did you
know her name?

01:20:50.583 --> 01:20:52.417
Still don't get
the big brain bit, do you?

01:20:52.417 --> 01:20:54.458
I'll see you tomorrow.
Feel good,

01:20:54.458 --> 01:20:57.208
you did very well.
See you.

01:21:19.125 --> 01:21:21.792
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:21:31.125 --> 01:21:32.625
Watch.
Here it comes again.

01:21:34.166 --> 01:21:35.750
GIRL: Mommy!

01:21:36.959 --> 01:21:38.250
Look at her go.

01:21:38.834 --> 01:21:40.667
(HORNS HONKING)

01:21:40.667 --> 01:21:42.250
(DOG BARKING)

01:21:46.083 --> 01:21:48.625
Going back for the cat
is wonderful.

01:21:48.834 --> 01:21:50.667
What kind of cat
was it, Julia?

01:21:50.667 --> 01:21:51.959
Persian.

01:21:52.291 --> 01:21:53.917
Oh. I love Persian.

01:21:59.542 --> 01:22:01.125
(BEEP)

01:22:02.667 --> 01:22:05.417
I'm sorry for the delay.
I just had to see that again.

01:22:05.417 --> 01:22:07.792
Oh, that's all right.
It's spectacular.

01:22:11.542 --> 01:22:12.750
I think that's
all for today.

01:22:12.750 --> 01:22:14.417
We'll meet
one more time tomorrow,

01:22:14.417 --> 01:22:16.333
mostly for
enjoyment's sake.

01:22:16.333 --> 01:22:18.000
Let's make it
around 1 o'clock.

01:22:22.667 --> 01:22:23.959
Hi!

01:22:24.667 --> 01:22:25.834
Great job.

01:22:25.834 --> 01:22:27.208
Great.

01:22:27.208 --> 01:22:29.208
Daniel, nice to see
you again. How are you?

01:22:29.208 --> 01:22:30.375
I'm fine.

01:22:30.375 --> 01:22:32.333
Good. You have
a good time tonight.
Thanks.

01:22:32.333 --> 01:22:34.208
I will see you
tomorrow at 1:00?
Okay.

01:22:34.208 --> 01:22:35.291
Bye-bye.

01:22:36.500 --> 01:22:38.000
Listen, Sam told me
about this amazing
Italian restaurant.

01:22:38.000 --> 01:22:39.166
What do you say?

01:22:39.166 --> 01:22:41.125
Very exciting stuff
up there, really.

01:22:41.667 --> 01:22:43.708
It was like watching
a Mutual of Omaha commercial.

01:22:44.250 --> 01:22:45.542
You're just jealous.

01:22:46.125 --> 01:22:48.041
You'll never know
how much.

01:22:49.041 --> 01:22:51.208
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:22:56.000 --> 01:22:57.542
Oh, my God!

01:22:58.792 --> 01:23:00.750
Those portions
are gigantic.

01:23:00.750 --> 01:23:02.750
Mmm. I'm so hungry.

01:23:02.750 --> 01:23:05.041
The residents
love this place.
This is supposed to be

01:23:05.041 --> 01:23:06.417
the best resident food
in the area.

01:23:06.417 --> 01:23:08.375
Really?
Good clumps, huh?
Mmm-hmm.

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:11.375
Enjoy your meal.
Thank you.

01:23:13.208 --> 01:23:15.208
So what was your
favorite food
in the whole world.

01:23:15.458 --> 01:23:17.750
Turkey with stuffing. Yeah.

01:23:17.750 --> 01:23:20.208
Really? I couldn't
eat turkey.
Why not?

01:23:20.208 --> 01:23:23.000
Well, when I was a kid
I had one as a pet,
and I named it.

01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:24.083
(CHUCKLES)

01:23:24.083 --> 01:23:25.708
And you can't eat
something you've named.

01:23:25.708 --> 01:23:27.583
I wish someone had
told me that years ago.

01:23:27.583 --> 01:23:29.291
I would have named
ice cream.

01:23:30.291 --> 01:23:31.458
Do you eat meat?

01:23:31.458 --> 01:23:33.625
Sometimes. Not often.
How about you?

01:23:33.959 --> 01:23:35.417
I like fish.

01:23:35.417 --> 01:23:37.041
Yeah, me, too.
What kind?

01:23:37.250 --> 01:23:39.750
Well, salmon,
and I like the kind

01:23:39.750 --> 01:23:42.583
that live near the
nuclear reactors,
in the rocks.

01:23:43.083 --> 01:23:44.542
I forget their name.

01:23:44.542 --> 01:23:45.917
(GIGGLES) Glow fish?

01:23:45.917 --> 01:23:48.125
That's right.
They'd light up your house
when you cook them.

01:23:48.125 --> 01:23:50.959
How are you? How was
your screening today?

01:23:50.959 --> 01:23:52.625
Very, very good,
thank you.

01:23:52.625 --> 01:23:54.000
